EntityDef.name: bgppeerfsmestablishedtransitions
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of times the #BGP# #FSM# is transitioned into the established state.

EntityDef.name: bgppeerintotalmessages
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of BGP messages received from the remote peer on this connection.

EntityDef.name: bgppeerinupdateelapsedtime
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the elapsed time, in seconds, since the last #BGP# UPDATE message was received from the peer. Each time the bgpPeerInUpdates counter is incremented the value of this object is set to zero.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: A network failure might have occured in the network. Investigate if there are any problems with the #IP# connectivity at the interface board.

EntityDef.name: bgppeerinupdates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #BGP# UPDATE messages received on this connection.

EntityDef.name: bgppeerouttotalmessages
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of BGP messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection.

EntityDef.name: bgppeeroutupdates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #BGP# UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of downlink #BSSGP# octets per #NSE#.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketssignalling
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of downlink #BSSGP# signalling packets per #NSE#.

EntityDef.name: bssgpstatusbvcunknown
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unknown #BVC# BSSGP-STATUS messages sent to the #BSC#. These messages are sent to the #BSC# when traffic, that is BSSGP-UL-UNITDATA messages, are received on the #PTP BVC#s that do not exist in the #SGSN-MME#. The traffic is then discarded. The #PTP BVC#s are non-existent in the #SGSN-MME# since no BVC-RESET messages, for the #PTP BVC#, have been received from the #BSC#.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the configuration. If no #PTP BVC# exists for incoming traffic it is probably because no BVC-RESET is received.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of IP packets being buffered due to flow control. This counter is increased when buffering IP packets and the BSS Cell bucket is full; the BSS MS bucket is full and when the BSS PFC bucket is full.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsbuffllcsuspend
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of IP packets buffered due to suspended Logical Link Control (LLC) between MS and SGSN.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsbuffllcsuspendededrx
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of IP packets buffered due to suspended Logical Link Control (LLC) between MS and SGSN for MS in Extended Idle Mode Discontinuous Reception (eDRX) mode. EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsbuffllcsuspendedpsm
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of IP packets buffered due to suspended Logical Link Control (LLC) between MS and SGSN for MS in Power Saving Mode (PSM). This measurement is a subset of the measurement from the counter bssgpDownlinkPacketsBuffLlcSuspend.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsbuffmobilesuspend
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This counter will be increased when buffering packets and the last reason for delay was the MS that has suspended GPRS.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsbuffsnapshot
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement is a snapshot of the number of IP packets currently being buffered. It is increased when bssgp.DownlinkPacketsBuff is stepped and decreased when a packet is removed from the buffer regardless if the packet is sent or discarded.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsdiscardllcsuspended

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsdiscardllcsuspendededrx
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of IP packets discarded due to suspended Logical Link Control (LLC) between MS and SGSN for MS in Extended Idle Mode Discontinuous Reception (eDRX) mode. This measurement is a subset of the measurement from the counter bssgpDownlinkPacketsDiscardLlcSuspended.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsdiscardllcsuspendedpsm
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of IP packets discarded due to suspended Logical Link Control (LLC) between MS and SGSN for MS in Power Saving Mode (PSM). This measurement is a subset of the measurement from the counter bssgpDownlinkPacketsDiscardLlcSuspended.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsdiscardedbucketfull
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of discarded IP packets due to Bucket Full. The counter is increased when the BSS Cell bucket is full, the BSS MS bucket is full, and when the BSS PFC bucket is full.

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsdiscardedbvcblocked

EntityDef.name: bssgpdownlinkpacketsdiscardedmobilesuspend
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded IP packets due to suspended mobile. This counter is increased when it is the MS that has suspended GPRS.

EntityDef.name: dnstimeouts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of timed-out DNS queries, that is, no response is received from any DNS server.
Note: This is measured on application level. On operating system level, the BIND DNS client retransmits the DNS query multiple times before the application times out. It is also possible that the retransmission continues after the application times out. Therefore, this counter does not correlate with the number of DNS queries that are sent externally toward the configured DNS server(s).
Note: The DNS query succeeds, if the DNS record is cached in the SGSN-MME. This is because the SGSN-MME indefinitely reuses the cached record when there is a timeout, even though the time-to-live value is exceeded.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: For more information on how to troubleshoot DNS connectivity, see DNS Related Faults in Troubleshooting.
The consequences of lost DNS connectivity are as follows: - DNS queries fail if the record is not cached. This can lead to major service outage. - DNS queries succeed if the record is cached, even after the record expires (time-to-live value exceeded). - All DNS queries fail as soon as the DNS cache is cleared. The DNS cache is cleared by a restart or an operator command. - DNS server provisioning does not have any effect until the DNS connectivity is restored.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_overloadprotectiondiscardedpagingmessage_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #S1AP# paging messages that have been discarded by the #SCTP# paging overload protection mechanism in order to avoid a potential overload of the SS7/SCTP DPs. Note that as long as the #CPU# load is not extremely high only a subset of the paging messages is discarded, and hence the paging procedure does not necessarily fail. Outgoing paging messages related to CS Fallback to WCDMA and GSM are not discarded by the #OLP# mechanism. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of overload and it is time to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more eNodeBs to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. If several paging messages are ignored, this could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network.
The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has ceased. For more information, see Troubleshooting.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignoredoutboundrequestshss
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of outgoing request messages toward the HSS that have been rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionss7messagereject
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of rejected outgoing request through #SS7# link. The counter is incremented when an outgoing request through #SS7# link is rejected. #SCCP# messages are discarded. #TCAP# messages are rejected with a reject message.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of #SS7# overload. The #SS7# bandwidth may need to be increased or the Ss7EffectiveBandwidth parameter may need to be adjusted to match available #SS7# bandwidth.
#SS7# overload may also occur after an #SGSN-MME# restart or a large restart, and the reattach rate may be so high that the system temporarily needs to reject #SS7# traffic to protect #SS7# links from overload. The alarm will be cleared as more and more subscribers are successfully attached in the #SGSN-MME# which results in decreased load on the #SS7# links. For more information, see Troubleshooting.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionrefuseds1aprequest
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of refused incoming S1AP requests. The counter is incremented when an incoming request is subject to OLP for the S1-MME interface. This will for example lead to failed Attach, Detach, Service Request or TAU. The OLP for the S1-MME interface is active on the SCTP devices.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold:
This is an indication of signaling overload in SGSN-MME. Consider reviewing the network dimensioning/configuration.
Note that the overload could be due to a temporary error in the network. Examples of this could be SGSN-MME restart, large restart or an eNodeB restart. It may also occur during temporary external communication problems towards for example the HSS, when causing the mobiles to retry their signaling (mainly attach) in a large scale. In this case the signaling rate may be so high that the system temporarily needs to ignore it to protect the APs from overload. The alarm will be cleared as more and more subscribers are successfully attached and/or have successfully finished their signaling towards the SGSN-MME, which results in decreased signaling load. If the reason for the alarm is temporary and well known, no actions need to be taken. For further details see Troubleshooting.
Moving one or more BSCs or RNCs (SGSN-MME deployment dependent) may also improve the situation, due to the fact that if the SGSN-MME is heavily loaded from the GSM or WCDMA side it affects the total load on the SGSN-MME, thus may decrease the signaling success on the LTE side also. When this alarm is raised and not cleared within a limited period of time, it could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignoredconnections
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This indexed measurement shows the number of messages discarded by the Application Processor OverLoad Protection (AP OLP). The index is the AP OLP Priority level assigned to the UE. The AP OLP mechanism discards messages based on OLP Priority levels.
There are two other measurements related to this measurement. These are:
- gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredExistingConnections which provides the number of discarded messages for UE having an existing connection, that is, a connection known by the MME. This measurement is independent of the OLP Priority level and is overlapping the measurement gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredConnections.
- gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredNewConnections which provides the number of discarded messages for UE that does not have an existing connection, that is, a connection unknown to the MME. This measurement is independent of the OLP Priority level and overlaps the measurement gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredConnections.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectioncpuignoredconnections
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded messages related to connections on the #AP#s due to high #CPU# or #SU# load. The counter is incremented when a message is discarded on an #AP#. An ignored request forces the initiator to resend the message.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignoredexistingconnections
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of discarded messages related to connections on the #AP#s. The counter is incremented when a request to an existing connection is discarded on an #AP#. An existing connection is a connection where the #MS#/#UE# is known in the #SGSN-MME#, but is currently not doing any control signaling. A discarded request forces the initiator to resend the message.
Three factors can cause the request to be discarded on the #AP#s. These are:
- high #CPU# or Scheduler Utilization (#SU#) load, - high memory usage or, - long queues.
High #CPU# load is visible in the #CPU# counters or detected internally in the #SGSN-MME# as long queue length to certain processes. Long queues can occur even if the #CPU# counter is not high, especially if the signaling comes in bursts.
There are three counters used for measuring the number of discarded messages for each attribute listed above. These are:
- gsnOverloadProtectionCPUIgnoredConnections, - gsnOverloadProtectionMemoryIgnoredConnections, - gsnOverloadProtectionQueueIgnoredConnections.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold:
- There is an indication of overload and the #SGSN-MME# must be offloaded by, for example, moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or eNodeBs to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. The threshold for this measurement type indicates a severe overload condition on the #SGSN-MME#.
- Overload can also occur after an #SGSN-MME# restart or recovery situation after a SW or HW fault. In this case the signaling rate can be so high that the system temporarily needs to reject signaling to protect the local #AP# from overload. It can also happen after restarts of external nodes when the #SGSN-MME# needs to take immediate action, such as eNodeB restart or #HLR#/#HSS# restart, or when external nodes regain connectivity, which can increase signaling due to resending information in the network.
The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has ceased. For more information, see Troubleshooting.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignorednewconnections
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of messages related to connections on the #AP#s. The counter is incremented when a request to a new connection is discarded on an #AP#. A new connection is a connection where the #MS#/#UE# is unknown in the #SGSN-MME#. A discarded request will lead to, for example, a failed attach or #ISRAU#.
Three factors can cause the request to be discarded on the #AP#s. These are:
- high #CPU# or Scheduler Utilization (#SU#) load, - high memory usage or, - long queues.
High #CPU# load is visible in the #CPU# counters or detected internally in the #SGSN-MME# as long queue length to certain processes. Long queues can occur when the #CPU# counter is not high, especially if the signaling comes in bursts.
The request can also be discarded due to lack of memory on a payload #DP#. The limit is set either by the #AP# handling the connection, or by the payload #DP# with the least free memory.
There are three counters used for measuring the number of discarded messages for each attribute listed above. These are:
- gnsOverloadProtectionCPUIgnoredConnections, - gnsOverloadProtectionMemoryIgnoredConnections, - gnsOverloadProtectionQueueIgnoredConnections.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold:
- There is an indication of overload and the #SGSN-MME# must be offloaded by, for example, moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or eNodeBs to an #SGSN-MME# with less load. If several new connections are ignored, then a network reconfiguration could be necessary. The threshold for ignored new connections is lower than for existing connections.
- Overload can also occur after an #SGSN-MME# restart or recovery situation after a SW or HW fault. In this case, the signaling rate can be so high that the system temporarily needs to reject signaling to protect the local #AP# from overload. It can also happen after restarts of external nodes when the #SGSN-MME# needs to take immediate action, such as eNodeB restart or #HLR#/#HSS# restart, or when external nodes regain connectivity, which can increase signaling due to resending information in the network.
The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has ceased. For more information, see Troubleshooting.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionmemoryignoredconnections
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded messages related to connections on the #AP#s due to high memory load. The counter is incremented when a message is discarded on an #AP#. An ignored request forces the initiator to resend the message.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionqueueignoredconnections
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded messages related to connections on the #AP#s due to high queue length on certain processes. The counter is incremented when a message is discarded on an #AP#. An ignored request forces the initiator to resend the message.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionrejectedduetodoics6a
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of rejected messages through S6a interface towards a remote node (HSS) due to an overload indication received from this remote node. The remote node defines the percentage of all incoming messages to be dropped. The counter is incremented when a message is rejected to satisfy the requested percentage. The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has subsided. For more information, see Overload Protection.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionrejectedduetodoict6a
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of rejected messages through T6a interface towards a remote node (SCEF) due to an overload indication received from this remote node. The remote node defines the percentage of all incoming messages to be dropped. The counter is incremented when a message is rejected to satisfy the requested percentage. The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has subsided. For more information, see Overload Protection.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionrefusedsccpconnectreq
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of refused incoming #SCCP# connection requests. The counter is incremented when an incoming request is subject to the #SS7# #OLP# for Incoming Traffic. This will lead to failed Attach, Detach, Service Request or #RAU#. The #SS7# #OLP# for incoming traffic is active on the #SS7# devices.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of signaling overload in #SGSN-MME#. It may be time to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example by moving one or more #RNC#s to an #SGSN-MME# with less signaling load. This alarm is raised only for connection oriented #SCCP# signaling for #WCDMA#. However moving one or more #BSC#s may also improve the situation, due to the fact that if the #SGSN-MME# is heavily loaded from the #GSM# side it affects the total load on the #SGSN-MME#, thus may decrease the signaling success on the #WCDMA# side also. When this alarm is raised and not cleared within a limited period of time, it could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network. Overload may also occur after a #SGSN-MME# restart, large restart or an #RNC# restart. It may also occur during temporary external communication problems towards for example the #HLR#, when causing the mobiles to retry their signaling (mainly attach) in a large scale. In this case the signaling rate may be so high that the system temporarily needs to ignore it to protect the #AP#s from overload. The alarm will be cleared as more and more subscribers are successfully attached and/or have successfully finished their signaling towards the #SGSN-MME#, which results in decreased signaling load. If the reason for the alarm is temporary and well known, no actions need to be taken. For further details see Troubleshooting.

EntityDef.name: gtp_indatapkts4

Note that the counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).

EntityDef.name: gtp_outdataocts4
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of octets in outgoing #GTP# data packets on the S4 interface. #Note: The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version. EntityDef.name: gtp_outdatapkts4
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #GTP# data #PDU#s which have been generated by the #GTP# protocol entity on the S4 interface. #Note: The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.Note#

EntityDef.name: gtp_payloadgtpuerrorpkt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of incoming #GTP# data packets where payload length indicated in #GTP# header is inconsistent with actual length. The #SGSN# receives a #GTP-U# packet from either the #RNC# or the #GGSN# and detects that the payload length indicated in the #GTP# header is inconsistent with the actual length. The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_attpagingforcssr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PS paging procedures initiated by the MME for MSC Triggered CS Service Restoration (CSSR). The counter is incremented when a PS paging procedure is started after UE Backup Retrieval procedure upon receipt of the SGsAP Paging Request message from the MSC with IMSI. It could happen after the serving MME is restarted and the UE CS/PS service has not been restored on the MME, or the SGsAP Paging Request is sent to an alternative MME in the pool. The counter is incremented at the sending of the paging message with the current S-TMSI in the procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_attpagingforntsr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PS paging procedures initiated by the MME for Network Triggered Service Restoration (NTSR). The counter is incremented when a PS paging procedure is started upon receipt of the Downlink Data Notification message from the SGW with IMSI. The counter is incremented at the sending of the paging message with the current S-TMSI in the procedure. Paging attempts for low-complexity UEs are also included.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_attpagingfortdr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PS paging procedures initiated by the MME for UE restoration upon Mobile-Terminated Non-IP Data Delivery over the SCEF. The counter is incremented each time the MME initiates a PS paging procedure when receiving an MT-Data-Request message from the SCEF. Paging attempts for low-complexity UEs are also included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_attachthrottlingnonreservedgranted_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Update Location Request (ULR) and Authentication Information Request (AIR) messages due to the UE Restoration procedure that have been accepted by the Attach throttle using the non-reserved allowance. The non-reserved allowance is the difference between the total Attach throttle allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter, and the sum of the reserved allowances, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach and MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitGeoredRestore parameters. ULR and AIR messages accepted using the reserved Geored allowance specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitGeoredRestore parameter are not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_ddnimsiatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of the received Downlink Data Notification (DDN) messages with IMSI. This counter is incremented each time a DDN message with IMSI is received from the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_ddnimsisucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge with IMSI. This counter is incremented each time a Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge message with IMSI and the cause "Request accepted" is sent out.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_pagingavoidedduetoueinedrx_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of paging procedures in EPS that have been avoided due to the UE being in eDRX during UE restoration upon the DDN with IMSI procedure or CS Service Restoration or Mobile-Terminated Non-IP Data Delivery over the SCEF in Geographically redundant pool. The counter is increased when paging is needed, but cannot be performed since the UE is in eDRX and not in paging time window.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_s6ablockbythrottle_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of S6a messages blocked due to the Attach Throttling function in the geographically redundant pool. The counter is incremented when an S6a message is blocked because the number of messages under throttling control exceeds the available allowance. The available allowance for Geographically Redundant UE Restoration messages is the difference between the total Attach throttle allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter and the reserved allowance for E-UTRAN attach procedures, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach parameter.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_sgspagingrelayrecd_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Echo Request messages with the "SGs Paging Request" operation code received over the S10 interface. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives an Echo Request message with the "SGs Paging Request" operation code over the S10 interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_sgspagingrelaysent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Echo Request messages with the "SGs Paging Request" operation code sent over the S10 interface. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends an Echo Request message with the "SGs Paging Request" operation code over the S10 interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupcreaterecd_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica creation messages received. This counter is incremented each time the Replication MME receives an Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Backup Required".

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupcreatesent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica creation messages sent . This counter is incremented each time the Serving MME sends Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Backup Required".

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupdeleterecd_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica deletion messages received. This counter is incremented each time the Replication MME receives an Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Delete Required".

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupdeletesent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica deletion messages sent. This counter is incremented each time the Serving MME sends Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Delete Required".

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupretrievalatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica retrieval attempts. This counter is incremented when the new MME trying to restore the UE service sends one or multiple Echo Request messages over the S10 interface with the operation code "Retrieval Request". The multiple retrieval messages are counted as one attempt.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupretrievalsent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of all Retrieval messages sent by the new MME. This counter is incremented each time the new MME sends an Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Retrieval Request". For one UE geo-replica retrieval attempt, multiple retrieval messages may be sent to different MMEs in the pool and they are all counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_geored_uebackupretrievalsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful UE geo-replica retrievals. This counter is incremented when the new MME trying to restore the UE service receives the successful Echo Response message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Retrieval Response".

EntityDef.name: ipforwdatagrams
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams for which this entity is not the final IPv4 destination, and so an attempt is made to find a route to forward the input datagrams to the IPv4 destination.
This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

EntityDef.name: ipforwardingtableentries
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv4 routes currently in the forwarding table.
The SCXB allows a maximum of 5000 IPv4 routes in the forwarding table of each IP network. Exceeding this limit causes loss of connectivity.
This measurement type is indexed by IP indexing option 2, MagId.SlotId.Network only.
Do the following when the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: - Reduce the number of static routes configured on the SGSN-MME. - Reduce the number of routes exported to the SGSN-MME from external routers. - If OSPF is used, consider using OSPF NSSA to reduce the number of routes.

EntityDef.name: ipfragcreates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at the indexed logical network.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipfragfails
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at the indexed logical network but could not be because, for example, their Don't Fragment flag was set.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipfragoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at the indexed logical network.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipinaddrerrors
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on the indexed logical network, because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was not a valid address. This count includes invalid addresses (for example, 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported classes (for example, Class E).
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipinhdrerrors
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity. This due to errors in their #IP# headers, such as version number mismatch, bad header length, bad #IP# total length. In addition, for packets designated to a router board, errors discovered in processing control flags, header checksum, and #IP# options are counted.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipinreceives
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams received on the indexed logical network, including those received in error.
This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

EntityDef.name: ipoutnoroutes
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number #IP# datagrams discarded, on the indexed logical network, because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in the ipForwDatagrams counter which meets this no-route criterion.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipreasmfails
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of failures (for any reason) detected by the #IP# reassembly algorithm for the indexed logical network. Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded #IP# fragments.
This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

EntityDef.name: ipreasmoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams successfully reassembled on the indexed logical network.
This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

EntityDef.name: ipreasmreqds
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# fragments received on the indexed logical network which needed to be reassembled at this entity.
This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

EntityDef.name: ipforwdatagrams
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams for which this entity is not the final IPv4 destination, and so an attempt is made to find a route to forward the input datagrams to the IPv4 destination.
This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

EntityDef.name: ipforwtableentriestotal
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of IPv4 routes currently in all forwarding tables on the LC.
The SGSN-MME has the following limits on route numbers: - The SMXB supports a total maximum of 40,000 IPv4 routes in all forwarding tables of each LC. - The SMXB has no limit on the number of IPv4 routes in the forwarding table of each IP network. Exceeding these limits causes loss of connectivity.
Do the following when the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: - Reduce the number of static routes configured on the SGSN-MME. - Reduce the number of routes exported to the SGSN-MME from external routers. - If OSPF is used, consider using OSPF NSSA to reduce the number of routes.

EntityDef.name: ipfragcreates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at the logical networks on this entity.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipfragfails
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at logical networks on this entity but could not be because, for example, their Don't Fragment flag was set.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipfragoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at all logical networks on this entity.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipinaddrerrors
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on the logical networks on this entity, because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was not a valid address. This count includes invalid addresses (for example, 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported classes (for example, Class E).
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipinhdrerrors
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity. This due to errors in their #IP# headers, such as version number mismatch, bad header length, bad #IP# total length. In addition, for packets designated to a router board, errors discovered in processing control flags, header checksum, and #IP# options are counted.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipinreceives
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.
This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

EntityDef.name: ipoutnoroutes
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams discarded, on all logical networks on this entity, because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in the ipForwDatagrams counter which meets this no-route criterion.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

EntityDef.name: ipreasmfails
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of failures (for any reason) detected by the #IP# reassembly algorithm for all logical networks on this entity. Note that this is not necessarily a count of the discarded #IP# fragments.
This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

EntityDef.name: ipreasmoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams successfully reassembled on all logical networks on this entity.
This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

EntityDef.name: ipreasmreqds
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IP# fragments received, for all logical networks on this entity, which needed to be reassembled at this entity.
This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

EntityDef.name: ipsystemstatsindiscards
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded. The reason can be a lack of buffer space, therefore no point to process further. This counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.
Note: This measurement counts GSM payload and signalling, and WCDMA payload. It is not supported on single-access LTE nodes.

EntityDef.name: ifindiscards
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of inbound packets that have been dropped due to lack of resources or denied by packet filtering. Lack of resources can for example be when packet queues are full, the driver is out of buffers, clusters or descriptors.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

EntityDef.name: ifinoctets
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

EntityDef.name: ifinpkts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

EntityDef.name: ifoutdiscards
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of packets that have been dropped due to lack of resources or denied by packet filtering. There can be a lack of resources when packet queues are full, or when the driver is out of buffers, clusters or descriptors.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

EntityDef.name: ifoutoctets
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

EntityDef.name: ifoutpkts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested to be transmitted.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

EntityDef.name: ifoutqlen
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the length of the output packet queue, in packets.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: The severity of the overload depends on the queue's length (the threshold value) and the overload frequency. If the threshold is reached often, it may indicate that either the network capacity or the load sharing needs to be improved.
This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the filter configuration. If that does not solve the problem, analysis of the inbound traffic may be necessary. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:

The counter value is only applicable for #IBAS# #IP# Interface PIUs. This counter is now deprecated.

Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecincorrectpackets
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# and #GRE# packets discarded in the #IPsec# engine.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds it's supervised threshold: Check the available #IPsec# and #GRE# measurement types. Most probably, an #SA# has not been set up as it should, either locally or on the sending side.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecissillegalspi
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of incoming #IPsec# and #GRE# packets for which no configuration is found in #SADB#.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the #IPsec# and #GRE# configuration. Most probably, an #SA# has not been set up as it should, either locally or on the sending side.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecissinokpackets
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# or #GRE# packets which has been processed correctly, coming in.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecissmd5mismatch
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of times the comparison between the given value and the calculated (with md5 algorithm) value did not match.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the #IPsec# configuration. Most probably the wrong authentication keys for one or more #SA#s are used. Many forms of data corruption, that is bit errors in the packets, can also cause the authentication to fail.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecissoutokpackets
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# and #GRE# packets which has been processed correctly, going out.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecisssha1mismatch
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of times the comparison between the given value and the calculated (through the sha1 algorithm) value did not match.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the #IPsec# configuration. Most probably the wrong authentication keys for one or more #SA#s are used. Many forms of data corruption, that is, bit errors in the packets, can also cause the authentication to fail.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipsecwapacketsprocessed
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# and #GRE# header events. The counter is incremented by one every time an #IPsec# or #GRE# header is added or removed.
Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: ipv4v6forwardinghwhosttableutilization
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows how many percent of the total number of available host routes in the Line Card (LC) L3 switching HW that are currently utilized (for all VPNs). This is applicable for both IPv4 and IPv6 since they share the same HW resource.
When the HW routing table is full, outbound traffic may be forwarded in SW which leads to a lower forwarding capacity.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold:
To minimize the number of routes and to decrease the HW table utilization, it is recommended to use OSPF NSSA or route aggregation in the site routers.

EntityDef.name: ipv4v6forwardinghwnettableutilization
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows how many percent of the total number of available network routes in the LC L3 switching HW that are currently utilized (for all VPNs). This is applicable for both IPv4 and IPv6 since they share the same HW resource. When the HW routing table is full, outbound traffic may be forwarded in SW which leads to a lower forwarding capacity.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold:
To minimize the number of routes and to decrease the HW table utilization, it is recommended to use OSPF NSSA or route aggregation in the site routers.

EntityDef.name: ipv6forwdatagrams
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input datagrams for which this entity is not the final #IPv6# destination, and so an attempt is made to find a route to forward the input datagrams to the #IPv6# destination.
This measurement counts signalling IPv6 packets.

EntityDef.name: ipv6forwardingtableentries
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv6 routes currently in the forwarding table.
The SCXB allows a maximum of 120 IPv6 routes in the forwarding table of each IP network. Exceeding this limit causes loss of connectivity.
This measurement type is indexed by IP indexing option 2, MagId.SlotId.Network only.
When the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold, reduce the number of static routes configured on the SGSN-MME.

EntityDef.name: ipv6inaddrerrors
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was not valid.
This measurement counts signalling IPv6 packets.

EntityDef.name: ipv6inhdrerrors
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity, due to errors in their #IP# headers. This includes version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, errors discovered in processing their #IP# options, and the like.
This measurement counts signalling IPv6 packets.

EntityDef.name: ipv6inreceives
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of input #IPv6# datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in errors.
This measurement counts signalling IPv6 packets.

EntityDef.name: ipv6intruncatedpkts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data.

EntityDef.name: ipv6outnoroutes
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of locally generated #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination.
This measurement counts signalling IPv6 packets.

EntityDef.name: ipv6forwtableentriestotal
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of IPv6 routes currently in all forwarding tables on the LC.
The SGSN-MME has the following limits on route numbers: - The SMXB supports a total maximum of 8,000 IPv6 routes in all forwarding tables of each LC. - The SMXB has no limit on the number of IPv6 routes in the forwarding table of each IP network. Exceeding these limits causes loss of connectivity.
Do the following when the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: - Reduce the number of static routes configured on the SGSN-MME. - Reduce the number of routes exported to the SGSN-MME from external routers.

Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of a high rate of automatic connection restarts of a single subscriber. Only if this continues over a longer period of time, there is need to further investigate the cause.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted location service request procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Sending the BSSGP Perform Location Request message to the #BSS# over the Gb interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestsucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful location service request procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Reception of the Perform Location Response message from the #BSS# over the Gb interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_lspagingatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted paging procedures due to the location service. The counter is incremented when a paging procedure is started due to location service, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by paging messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new location service from a GMLC is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with IMSI (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_lspagingsucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to location service, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to location service, is successfully concluded.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement type counts the number of Intra #PS# Handover attempts, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of #PS# Handover Required #BSSGP# message from #BSS# when Target #RA# is situated under own #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: hho_attoptintrasgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement type counts the number of Optimized PS Handover attempts, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of PS Handover Complete BSSGP message from BSS when no PS Handover Required has been received.

EntityDef.name: hho_succintersgsnnew
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement type counts the number of successful Inter PS Handover procedures in new SGSN. Trigger: Sending of Forward Relocation Complete GTP-C message to sourceSGSN GSM.

EntityDef.name: hho_succintersgsnold
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement type counts the number of successful PS Handover procedures in old SGSN. Trigger: Reception of Forward Relocation Complete GTP-C message from targetSGSN GSM.

EntityDef.name: hho_succintrasgsn

EntityDef.name: hho_succoptintrasgsn

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_intrammefailrr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-MME S1-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Roaming Restrictions.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_intrammefailrs_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-MME S1-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Regional Subscription.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s10nbrtempblockedtargetmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times an unavailable target MME is temporarily blacklisted for the inter-MME PS handover procedure over the S10 interface during the measurement period. The counter is measured on the source MME and increments every time the handover procedure fails to recieve a Forward Relocation Response from a target MME. When this happens the unavailable target MME is temporarily blacklisted and is not selected as a candidate target for the subsequent PS handover procedures for a default duration of 10 minutes (maximum 360 minutes).

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s10nbrunblockedtargetmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times a blacklisted target MME is removed from the blacklist and is again available for the inter-MME PS handover procedures over the S10 interface during the measurement period.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intermmeattsourcemme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the Handover Required arrives at the source MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intermmeatttargetmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when Forward Relocation Request arrives at the target MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intermmefailduetoapnrestrictiontargetmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Inter-MME Handover procedures over the S1 interface that have failed due to APN restriction in the target MME. The counter is incremented when a Forward Relocation Response message with a failure cause is sent to the source MME because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context of the Forward Relocation Request message received from the source MME are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the target MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intermmesuccsourcemme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter MME Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the Forward Relocation Complete Notification arrives at the source MME from the target MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intermmesucctargetmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter MME Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the Handover Notify message arrives at the target MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intermmetargetmmedecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-MME S1-based handover procedures, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported by the target MME, but the handover procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s1intrammefailduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Intra-MME Handover procedures over the S1 interface that have failed due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when a Handover Preparation Failure message with a failure cause is sent to the source eNB because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context stored for the UE are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_x2att_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted X2-based Handover procedures. Trigger: Receiving the S1-AP Path Switch Request message from the target eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_x2fail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed X2-based Handover procedures. Trigger: Sending the S1-AP Path Switch Request Failure message to the target eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_x2failduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of X2-based Handover procedures that have failed due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when a Path Switch Request Failure message with a failure cause is sent to the target eNB because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context stored for the UE are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_x2failrr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful X2-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Roaming Restrictions.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_x2failrs_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful X2-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Regional Subscription.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_x2succ_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful X2-based Handover procedures. Trigger: Sending the S1-AP Path Switch Request Acknowledge message to the target eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_fromumtsfailinterduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Inter-Node IRAT Handover procedures from UMTS to LTE that have failed due to APN restriction in the target MME. The counter is incremented when a Forward Relocation Response message with a failure cause is sent to the source 3G SGSN because all the APNs in the PDP Context of the Forward Relocation Request message received from the source 3G SGSN are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the target MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_fromumtsfailintraduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Intra-Node IRAT Handover procedures from UMTS to LTE that have failed due to APN restriction in the MME part of the combined node. The counter is incremented when an Intra-Node IRAT Handover procedure from UMTS to LTE fails because all the APNs in the PDP Context stored for the UE from the 3G SGSN part of the combined node are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME part.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_fromumtsinterdecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-SGSN-MME IRAT PS handover procedures from UMTS to LTE, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported by the target MME, but the handover procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_fromumtsintradecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN-MME IRAT PS handover procedures from UMTS to LTE, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported by the target MME, but the handover procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_fromumtssuccintra_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful intra-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #UMTS# access to #LTE# access. The counter increases when the #MME# receives a Handover Notify message from the eNodeB. The counter is measured on the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_s3nbrtempblockedtargets4sgsn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times an unavailable target S4-SGSN is blacklisted during IRAT PS handover procedures over the S3 interface during the measurement period. The counter is measured on the source MME and increments every time the handover procedure fails to recieve a Forward Relocation Response from a target S4-SGSN. When this happens the unavailable target S4-SGSN is temporarily blacklisted and is not available as a candidate target for the subsequent PS handover procedures for a default duration of 10 minutes (maximum 360 minutes).

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_s3nbrunblockedtargets4sgsn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times a blacklisted target S4-SGSN is removed from the blacklist and is again available for the IRAT PS handover procedures over S3 interface during the measurement period.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_toumtsattintra_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter increases when the #MME# receives a Handover Required message with RNC Target ID. The counter is measured on the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_umtsattinc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #UMTS# to #LTE#. The counter is incremented when the Forward Relocation Request message arrives at the target #MME# from the source #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_umtsattout_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #LTE# to #UMTS#. The counter is incremented when the Handover Required message arrives at the source #MME# with the Handover Type #IE# set to "LTEtoUTRAN".

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_umtssuccinc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #UMTS# to #LTE#. The counter is incremented when the Handover Notify message arrives at the target #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_umtssuccout_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #LTE# to #UMTS#. The counter is incremented when the Forward Relocation Complete Notification message arrives at the source #MME# from the target #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_lteattinc_u

EntityDef.name: vs_iratho_ltesuccinc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful incoming inter-#SGSN#/#MME# #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU with emergency indication is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_emcintratauuscdiscarded_e

The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU with emergency indication is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intertauipmrrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful ISC SGSN-MME TAU procedures that are caused by the Inter-PLMN Mobility Restriction function.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intertaunascongestioncontrolrejected_e

The MME sends the reject messages in response to the Inter-SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU Request with Inter System Change due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intertauuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intertauuscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intertaurejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Inter-Node TAU Inter-System Change from SGSN procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the new MME. The counter is incremented when a TAU Reject message is sent to the UE because all the APNs in the PDP Context of the SGSN Context Response message received from the old SGSN are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the new MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intrataunascongestioncontrolrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to the Intra-SGSN-MME TAU Request with Inter System Change due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intratauuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intratauuscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_intrataurejectduetoapnrestriction_e

The counter is incremented when a TAU Reject message is sent to the UE because all the APNs in the PDP Context stored for the UE from the SGSN part of the combined node are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME part.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinteratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #TAU# from both #GnSGSN# and from #S4-SGSN# procedures. Both sent and resent messages from #UE# are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterdecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Inter-SGSN-MME TAU with ISC, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched, but the TAU procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterdecorreject_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Inter-SGSN-MME TAU with ISC that are rejected because the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched in the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterdecorreroutein_e

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_11_e

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_12_e

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_13_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_14_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_15_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_9_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #9, "UE identity cannot be derived by the network".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of failed inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures from #SGSN-MME# procedures (with #RAT# change). Failed TAU, both from #Gn-SGSN# and from #S4-SGSN#, are counted. Both sent and resent messages from the #UE# are counted.
This will count inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinterfailnoctxt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed #TAU# from #Gn-SGSN# and #S4-SGSN# procedures due to the old #SGSN# not sending #PDP# context or #PDN# connections respectively.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinters3att_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-node #ISC# #TAU# from #S4-SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change). Both sent and resent messages from the #UE# are counted. If the MME can not find any #S4-SGSN#s, it is impossible to determine which type of #SGSN# made the attempt. Therefore attempts that fail because the #MME# is unable to find an #SGSN#, are not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauinters3succ_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed inter-node #ISC# #TAU# from #S4-SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change).The counter is incremented when the #TAU# Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintersucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #TAU# from both #GnSGSN# and #S4-SGSN# procedures.The counter is incremented when the #TAU# Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintersuccwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful inter-node ISC TAU procedures, after which the UE is in the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintraatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures from #SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change). Both sent and resent messages from the #UE# are counted. This will count intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures both from #Gn-SGSN# and from #S4-SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintradecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN-MME TAU with ISC, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched, but the TAU procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintradecorreject_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN-MME TAU with ISC that are rejected because the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched in the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintradecorreroutein_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN-MME TAU with ISC, where the MME receives a rerouted Initial UE Message with MMEGI from another DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintradecorrerouteout_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN-MME TAU with ISC, where the MME sends a Reroute NAS Request message to the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrafail_11_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrafail_12_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrafail_13_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrafail_14_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrafail_15_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrafail_40_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #40, "No EPS bearer context activated".

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrasucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-node #ISC# #TAU# from #SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change). The counter is incremented when a #TAU# Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#. This will count successful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# from both #Gn-SGSN# and from #S4-SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_tauintrasuccwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful intra-node ISC TAU procedures, after which the UE is in the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection.

EntityDef.name: isysc_unsuccintrasgsngsmumtsraucspscoord
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN inter-system change procedures being rejected due to the coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a MOCN constellation.

EntityDef.name: isysc_unsuccintrasgsnumtsgsmraucspscoord
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Intra-SGSN ISC procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_rauuscdiscarded_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The number of Inter-SGSN Inter-System Change RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_rauuscdiscarded_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The number of Inter-SGSN Inter-System Change RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_isysc_rauuscrejected_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Inter-SGSN RAU Inter-System Change that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Inter-SGSN RAU Inter-System Change is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbractattachedsubusimra
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers using USIM per RA within an SGSN. It includes the attached USIM users with GSM access and UMTS access. This gauge is incremented when a USIM subscriber is attached and decremented when it is detached. For an RA Update, the old RA indexed gauge is decremented and the new RA indexed gauge is incremented.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_nbractattachedsub_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs that are NB-IoT devices and leave or enter the AP within an MME area with RAT type NB. The gauge is incremented when the UE enters the state emm_registered, for example, because of Attach, Inter-MME TA Update, Detach, or Implicit Detach. The gauge is decremented when the UE leaves the state emm_registered. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attattach_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within the MME's area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attdetachduetopgwresel_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times of detaching UE triggered by the MME due to PGW reselection.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attdetachhsspcscfinit_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of the Detach attempts, triggered by an Insert Subscriber Data Request message where the P-CSCF Restoration Request bit is set.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attdetachmme
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MME#-initiated #EPS# detach requests, node total. It is incremented each time a detach request is sent from the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attdetachue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #UE#-initiated #E-UTRAN# detach procedures within this #MME# area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attenodeblistpaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of paging procedures based on the latest visited eNodeB list. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request message is sent to eNodeBs in the latest visited eNodeB list. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LatestVisitedENodeBList within a paging profile. Retransmission of a Paging Request message based on the latest visited eNodeB list is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attimsidetachmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MME-initiated IMSI detach procedures. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends an IMSI detach request to the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attlastvisitedenodebpaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the eNodeB a #UE# has visited. That is at the transmission of the first paging message attempt in a paging selection of LastVisitedENodeB within a paging profile. Retransmission of Paging Request based on last visited eNodeB is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attlastvisitedtapaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement gives the total number of attempted paging procedures based on last visited #TA#. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the last #TA#. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LastVisitedTA within a paging profile. Retransmission of Paging Request based on last visited #TA# is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attpspaging_e
