EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #MME# over the #S1-MME# interface. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #S-TMSI#. Optionally, the paging procedure is followed by paging messages with the old #S-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new Downlink Data Indication from the Serving Gateway is regarded as a new procedure. Note: Paging procedures triggered by NTSR or CSSR are not counted in this counter. Paging procedures triggered by NTSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForNTSR.E. Paging procedures triggered by CSSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForCSSR.E.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attservicerequest_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted S1 Service request procedures in the MME. It is incremented when an S1 Service Request is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_atttalistpaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement gives the total number of attempted paging procedures based on whole #TAI# list a #UE# has registered. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the whole #TAI# list. That is, at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of #TAI# list within a paging profile. Retransmission of Paging Request based on #TAI# list is not counted. Note: Paging procedures triggered by NTSR or CSSR are not counted in this counter. Paging procedures triggered by NTSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForNTSR.E. Paging procedures triggered by CSSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForCSSR.E.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachconnectionsuspendatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Attach procedures for which the UE has requested to use the Connection Suspend and Resume feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachconnectionsuspendsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Attach procedures for which the UE is granted use of the Connection Suspend and Resume feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachcpbyconfigwhenuerequp_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Attach Procedures with the SGi IP PDN connection established over control plane because the MME local policy permits control plane for the UE supporting the control plane CIoT EPS optimization and S1-U data transfer while the UE prefers user plane CIoT EPS optimization.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachdecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attach request procedures, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched, but the attach procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachdecorreject_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attach request procedures that are rejected because the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched in the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachdecorreroutein_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attach request procedures, where the MME receives a rerouted Initial UE Message with MMEGI from another DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachdecorrerouteout_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attach request procedures, where the MME sends a Reroute NAS Request message to the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachdonasatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Attach procedures, where the UE has requested to use the 'Data over NAS' feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachdonassucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Attach Procedures, where the UE is granted use of the 'Data over NAS' feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachemcatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within this #MME# area, with emergency indication.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachemcsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within this #MME# area, with emergency indication. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an Attach Complete message.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachlapiatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Attach Requests sent from the low access priority UE to the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachlapirejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Attach Requests from the low access priority UE when the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control is activated.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachnascongestioncontrolrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Attach Request due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachrejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Attach procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when an Attach Reject combined with a PDN Connectivity Reject message is sent to the UE because the resolved APN is restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachrejectduetoattachthrottling_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of E-UTRAN attach procedures that have been rejected due to the Attach Throttling function. The counter is incremented when an Attach procedure is rejected because the available allowance has been exceeded. The available allowance for E-UTRAN attach procedures is the difference between the total Attach throttle allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter and the reserved allowance for Geographically Redundant UE Restoration Procedures specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitGeoredRestore parameter.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachsuccwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Attach procedures, after which the attached UE is in the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachthrottlingnonreservedgrantedattach_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of E-UTRAN attach procedures that have been accepted by the Attach throttle using the non-reserved allowance. The non-reserved allowance is the difference between the total Attach throttle allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter, and the sum of the reserved allowances, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach and MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitGeoredRestore parameters. E-UTRAN attach procedures accepted using the reserved Attach allowance specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach parameter are not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachupbyconfigwhenuereqcp_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Attach Procedures with the SGi IP PDN connection established over user plane because the MME local policy permits user plane for the UE supporting the control plane CIoT EPS optimization and S1-U data transfer while the UE prefers control plane CIoT EPS optimization.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachuscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachwithesmdummyatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Attach procedures with an ESM dummy message contained in the ESM message container IE in the Attach Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachwithesmdummysucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Attach procedures with an ESM dummy message contained in the ESM message container IE in the Attach Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_connectionresume_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Connection Resume procedures. The counter is incremented when an S1-AP UE Context Resume Request message or an S1-AP Path Switch Request with RRC Cause Resume is received from the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_connectionresumefailure_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Connection Resume procedures. The counter is incremented when an S1-AP UE Context Resume Failure message is sent in response to an S1-AP UE Context Resume Request message. It is also incremented when an X2-based Handover procedure with RRC Cause Resume is rejected or aborted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_connectionresumefailureduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Resume procedures that have failed due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when an S1-AP UE Context Resume Failure message is sent to the eNodeB or an X2-based Handover procedure with RRC Cause Resume is rejected or aborted because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context stored for the UE are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_connectionsuspend_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Suspend procedures. The counter is incremented when an S1-AP UE Context Suspend Request message is received from the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_controlplaneservicereqnascongestioncontrolrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Control Plane Service Request due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_controlplaneservicerequestatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Control Plane Service Request procedures. It is incremented when an S1 Control Plane Service Request message is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_controlplaneservicerequestfail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessfulControl Plane Service Request procedures. It is incremented when an S1 Service Reject message is sent in response to a Control Plane Service Request.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_cpsrrejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Control Plane Service Request procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when a Service Reject message is sent to the UE because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context stored for the UE are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_csfbpagingatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #CS# fallback paging procedures due to #MT# call, initiated at the #MME# over the S1-MME interface. The counter is incremented when a #CS# fallback paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current S-TMSI. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #MT# call from an #MSC/VLR# is regarded as a new procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_csfbpagingsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to #MT# call, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to #CS# fallback, is successfully concluded.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_csfbtowgatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #CS# fallback procedures to #WCDMA# or #GSM#, in the #MME#. It is incremented either when an extended service request for a Mobile Originated #MO# call is received from the #UE# or when a paging request for an #MT# call is received from the #MSC/VLR# over the SGs interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_csfbtowgsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #CS# fallback procedures to #WCDMA# or #GSM#, in the #MME#. It is incremented each time a #CS# fallback procedure is successfully concluded, at the reception of a #UE# context release complete message.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_csgaccessatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts by UE to access CSG cells.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_csgaccessfail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed attempts by UE to access CSG cells due to CSG restrictions.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_emcattachuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_emcextservicerequscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages with emergency indication that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message with emergency indication is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_emcintertauuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of inter-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_emcintratauuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of intra-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_emcservicerequscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_11_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #11, "#PLMN# not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_12_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_13_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_14_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #14, "#EPS# Services not allowed in this #PLMN#".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_15_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_17_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #17, "Network failure".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_19_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 19 (ESM failure).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_5_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 5 (IMEI not accepted).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_6_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed attach procedures per #MME# due to a blocked #ME#. It is incremented when the #MME# returns an Attach Reject message to the #UE# with cause code #6, Illegal #ME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_7_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #7, "EPS Services not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_epsattachfail_8_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #8, "EPS Services and non EPS Services not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_extservicerequscdetached_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_extservicerequscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_extservicerequscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_extendedservicereqatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Extended Service Request procedures for 1xCS fallback to 1xRTT in the #MME#. It is incremented when an Extended Service Request is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_extendedservicereqfail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Extended Service Request procedures for 1xCS fallback to 1xRTT in the #MME#. It is incremented when a Service Reject message is sent in response to an Extended Service Request.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_imeisvchange_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of events that the IMEISV of a UE changes. The counter is incremented when the MME detects IMEISV change of a UE, either by Security Mode Command or by Identity Request messages. The counter is not incremented when the MME gets the IMEISV of a UE at the first time.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmeintersgwtauatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives a Context Response message and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the new MME receives a TAU Request message after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmeintersgwtausucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever a normal Inter-MME TAU with SGW Relocation procedure is completed. It is also increased whenever the TAU is performed successfully after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmeintrasgwtauatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the new MME receives a Context Response message and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the new MME receives a TAU Request message after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmeintrasgwtausucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever a normal Inter-MME TAU procedure without SGW relocation is completed. It is also increased whenever the Inter-MME TAU is performed successfully after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmetaudecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-MME TAU procedures, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched, but the TAU procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmetaudecorreject_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-MME TAU procedures that are rejected because the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched in the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmetaudecorreroutein_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-MME TAU procedures, where the MME receives a rerouted Initial UE Message with MMEGI from another DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intermmetaudecorrerouteout_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-MME TAU procedures, where the MME sends a Reroute NAS Request message to the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intertauipmrrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Inter-MME TAU procedures that are caused by the Inter-PLMN Mobility Restriction function.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intertaunascongestioncontrolrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Inter-TAU Request due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intertauuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of inter-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intertauuscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter-MME TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter-MME TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intertaurejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Inter-MME TAU procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the new MME. The counter is incremented when a TAU Reject message is sent to the UE because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context of the Context Response message received from the old MME are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the new MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammeintersgwtauatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the Security Function is completed and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Request message after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammeintersgwtausucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation.The counter is increased whenever a normal Intra-MME TAU procedure with SGW relocation is completed. It is also increased whenever the Intra-MME TAU is performed successfully after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammeintrasgwtauatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the Security Function is completed and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Request message after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammeintrasgwtausucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever a normal Intra-MME TAU procedure without SGW relocation is completed. It is also increased whenever the Intra-MME TAU is performed successfully after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammetaudecoracceptunsuppue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-MME TAU procedures, where the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched, but the TAU procedure is handled by the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammetaudecorreject_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-MME TAU procedures that are rejected because the UE Usage Type is not locally supported or MMEGI is mismatched in the current DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammetaudecorreroutein_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-MME TAU procedures, where the MME receives a rerouted Initial UE Message with MMEGI from another DCN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrammetaudecorrerouteout_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-MME TAU procedures, where the MME sends a Reroute NAS Request message to the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrataunascongestioncontrolrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Intra-TAU Request due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intratauuscdetached_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra-MME TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra-MME TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intratauuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of intra-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intratauuscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra-MME TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra-MME TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrataurejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Intra-MME TAU with Active Flag or Signalling Active Flag procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when a TAU Reject message is sent to the UE because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context stored for the UE are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreport_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Report messages received in the #MME# from the eNodeB. Note: The counter can be used in the Cell Change Reporting feature, Mobility-Based Policy feature, and Presence Reporting Area Support feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportcontrolchangeofservicecell_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Reporting procedures initiated by the MME due to the change of a service cell. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Location Reporting Control or Handover Request message with the "Change of Service Cell" request type. Note: The counter can be used in the Cell Change Reporting feature, Mobility-Based Policy feature, and Presence Reporting Area Support feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportcontrolmtlr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Reporting Control messages sent by the #MME# to the eNodeB during Mobile Terminated Location Request procedures.This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Location Reporting Control message to the eNodeB during a Mobile Terminated Location Request procedure. Note: If another procedure has already sent the Location Reporting Control message to the eNodeB, the MME saves signaling by not re-sending the message. But this counter is still incremented in this case.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportfailurechangeofservicecell_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Location Reporting procedures initiated by the MME due to the change of a service cell. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a Location Report Failure Indication message during Location Reporting procedure for the "Change of Service Cell" request type. Note: The counter can be used in the Cell Change Reporting feature, Mobility-Based Policy feature, and Presence Reporting Area Support feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportfailuremtlr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Report Failure Indication messages received by the #MME# from the eNodeB during Mobile Terminated Location Request procedures. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a Location Report Failure Indication message from the eNodeB during a Mobile Terminated Location Request procedure. Note: If this measurement is not equal to the value of VS.MM.LocationReportMtlr.E subtracted from VS.MM.LocationReportControlMtlr.E, that is because no response is received from the eNodeB or for some other reasons.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportmtlr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Report messages received by the #MME# from the eNodeB during Mobile Terminated Location Request procedures. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a Location Report message from the eNodeB during a Mobile Terminated Location Request procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Location Update procedures towards an #MSC/VLR#, initiated within the #MME#. This counter is incremented each time a Location Update procedure is started towards an #MSC/VLR#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationupdatesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Location Update procedures towards an #MSC/VLR#, initiated within the #MME#. This counter is incremented each time a Location Update procedure is successfully concluded towards an #MSC/VLR#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mocsfbattinnocsservicearea_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of MO CS call attempts when the CombinedRegistrationSetting parameter is set to dummy_cs_service and the #UE# is in no CSFB service area. This counter is incremented each time an MO CS call is rejected because of no CSFB service area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mosmsattinnocsservicearea_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of MO SMS attempts when the CombinedRegistrationSetting parameter is set to dummy_cs_service and the #UE# is in no CS service area. This counter is incremented each time an MO SMS is ignored because of no CS service area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbpagingatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted Paging procedures initiated for UEs in Tracking Areas with RAT type NB-IoT. The counter is incremented when a Paging message is sent to the eNodeB at the first transmission. Retransmissions of the same Paging message are not counted. Note: Paging procedures triggered by NTSR or CSSR are not counted in this counter. Paging procedures triggered by NTSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForNTSR.E. Paging procedures triggered by CSSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForCSSR.E.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbpagingsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures initiated for UEs in Tracking Areas with RAT type NB-IoT. This measurement is incremented irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Control Plane Service Request message, or any NAS message, is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedemc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of currently attached #UE# within this #MME# area for #IMS# Emergency Service only. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when the #UE# enters or leaves the #MME# with only #IMS# Emergency Service, for example, due to Attach, Inter-#MME# mobility, Detach or Implicit Detach. This gauge will also be increased if an attached user with an additional EMC PDN looses its non-emergency PDNs due to, for example, Roaming restrictions, and then ends up with only IMS Emergency Service.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedemcunauth_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of currently unauthenticated attached UEs within this MME area for IMS emergency service only. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when an unauthenticated UE enters or leaves the MME with only IMS Emergency Service, for example, due to Attach, Inter-MME mobility, Detach or Implicit Detach.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached #EPS# subscribers within this #MME# area. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when the #UE# enters or leaves the #MME#, for example, due to Attach, Inter-#MME# #TA# Update, Detach or Implicit Detach.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedsubcatm1_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs that are Cat-M1 and leave or enter the #AP# within an #MME# area. The gauge is incremented when the UE enters the state emm_registered and the #UE# is a Cat-M1 device, or when the #UE# is in the emm_registered state and the #MME# identifies the #UE# as a Cat-M1 device. The #MME# identifies a #UE# as a Cat-M1 device when it receives a UE CAPABILITY INFO INDICATION message indicating that the #UE# is a Cat-M1 device. The transmission of the UE CAPABILITY INFO INDICATION message is triggered by, for example, Attach, Handover, or Service Request.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedsubconnectionsuspend_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs granted use of the Connection Suspend and Resume feature. The gauge is incremented when a UE granted use of the Connection Suspend and Resume feature attaches to or moves into the MME. The gauge is decremented when a UE granted use of the Connection Suspend and Resume feature detaches from or moves out of the MME.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedsubdonas_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs using the 'Data over NAS' feature. The gauge is incremented when a UE using the 'Data over NAS' feature attaches to or moves into the MME. The gauge is decremented when a UE using the 'Data over NAS' feature detaches from or moves out of the MME.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbractattachedsublapi_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached UEs that are configured for low access priority. The gauge is incremented or decremented when the low access priority UE enters or leaves the MME, for example, due to Attach, Inter-MME TA Update, Detach or Implicit Detach.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrattachednr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached #NR# capable and not #NR# restricted #UEs#. The gauge is incremented when an #NR# capable and not #NR# restricted #UE# enters the #MME#. The gauge is decremented when an #NR# capable and not #NR# restricted #UE# leaves the #MME#.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrattachednrcapable_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached #NR# capable #UEs#. The gauge is incremented when an #NR# capable #UE# enters the #MME#. The gauge is decremented when an #NR# capable #UE# leaves the #MME#.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrattachedpsm_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #UEs# currently in Power Saving Mode (PSM). The gauge is incremented when a #UE# enters PSM, that is when the active timer expires and the implicit detach timer is started. The gauge is decremented when a #UE# leaves PSM, that is when any kind of signaling from the #UE# is received or when the #UE# is implicitly detached.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrconnectionsuspendedsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of suspended UE contexts. The gauge is incremented when a UE context is suspended as a result of a successful Connection Suspend procedure. The gauge is decremented when a UE context is resumed as a result of a successful Connection Resume procedure, or when the MME receives signaling from the UE. It is also decremented when a UE context is released as a result of an S1 Release procedure, or when the UE is detached.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrcsattachedsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the current number of SGs associated subscribers within this #MME#. The gauge is incremented at each successful initial registration for a #UE# towards an #MSC/VLR#. The gauge is decremented each time a #UE# is #IMSI# detached.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrdisconnectedenodeb_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently disconnected eNodeBs.
#Note: The Default alarm-triggering level and the Default alarm-clearing level for this gauge is updated according to the latest configured MaxEnodeBUnreachableAlarms value after a small restart.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrecmconnectedsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of subscribers in the ECM-CONNECTED state.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrhomesub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #EPS# home subscribers located in the MME location register. The #EMM# state of this subscriber is EMM_REGISTERED or EMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #EPS# subscribers that are homed in the same #EPS# network are considered.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrsdsattachedsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of subscribers on the MME that are registered on an SDS GW through the SGs-Lite interface. The gauge is incremented when a UE newly registers in the MME and the MME receives an SGSLite-LOCATION-UPDATE-ACK message with cause code "success" from an SDS GW, for example, in the Attach, Inter-TAU, GEO recovery, and Move (target side) procedures. The gauge is decremented when the MME sends an SGSLite-IMSI-DETACH-INDICATION message to an SDS GW.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note# Note: This gauge is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrsmsinmmeregisteredsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of registered subscribers for which the MME has successfully performed the SMS in MME registration.
The gauge is incremented in one of the following scenarios: - When a new subscriber registers on the MME, the MME successfully performs the SMS in MME registration for the subscriber. - A subscriber has already registered on the MME without the SMS in MME registration. Later, in the mobility procedure the MME successfully performs the SMS in MME registration for the subscriber, for example, when the UE requests SMS service and/or the configuration changes. - A subscriber reattaches to the MME after a proper detach, and the MME had successfully performed the SMS in MME registration for the subscriber in the previous registration.
The gauge is decremented in one of the following scenarios: - The MME sends a Notify Request message with the Removal of MME Registration for SMS bit set in the NOR-Flags AVP, to the HSS. - The MME receives an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the Remove SMS Registration bit set in the IDR-Flags AVP, from the HSS. - A subscriber moves to another SGSN-MME. - A subscriber is detached.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrsubemmregisteredwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs in the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection. The gauge is incremented when the UE changes into the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection, because of, for example, Attach, Inter-MME TAU procedures without PDN connection, or deactivation of the last PDN connection. The gauge is decremented when the UE leaves the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection, because of, for example, Detach or Inter-MME mobility procedures or Implicit Detach, or activation of the first PDN connection for the UE in EMM-REGISTERED.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrsubsupportemmregisteredwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs supporting EMM-REGISTERED without PDN connection. The gauge is incremented when the UE supporting EMM-REGISTERED without PDN connection changes into the EMM-REGISTERED state, because of, for example, Attach or Inter-MME TAU procedures. The gauge is decremented when the UE supporting EMM-REGISTERED without PDN connection changes into the EMM-DEREGISTERED state leaves the EMM-REGISTERED state, because of, for example, Detach or Implicit Detach or Inter-MME mobility procedures.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrvisitingforeign_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of international roaming subscribers in the #MME#, where the #MCC# in the #IMSI# number is not part of the #PLMN#s supported by the #MME#. The #EPS# #MM# state of these subscribers is EMM_REGISTERED or EMM_DEREGISTERED. #Note: Home subscribers with different #MCC#s included in the #IMSI# number and accessing #TAI# are also counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrvisitingnatsub_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of national roaming subscribers in the #MME#, where the #MCC# in the #IMSI# number is one of the #MCC#s of the #PLMN#s supported by the #MME#. The #EPS# #MM# state of these subscribers is EMM_REGISTERED or EMM_DEREGISTERED. #Note: Home subscribers with the same #MCC#s but different #MNC#s included in the #IMSI# number and accessing #TAI# are also counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nonbroadcastedlaiused_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times for which the Old location area identifier IE is filled with the non-broadcasted LAI in the Location Update Request message sent from the MME to an MSC.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pagingavoidedduetoueinpsm_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of paging procedures in #EPS# that have been avoided due to the #UE# being in Power Saving Mode (PSM). The counter is increased when paging is needed, but cannot be performed since the #UE# is in PSM and unreachable.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pagingavoidedingeoduetoueinedrx_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of paging procedures in #EPS# that have been avoided due to the #UE# being in eDRX during UE restoration upon the DDN with IMSI procedure in Geographically redundant pool. The counter is increased when paging is needed, but cannot be performed since the #UE# is in eDRX and not in paging time window after the MME receives a DDN message from the SGW. This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pspagingbypassquarantinetimeratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted PS Paging procedures that meet the following conditions: - The PS Paging procedure is triggered by a DDN message. - The MME starts the PS Paging procedure by bypassing the paging quarantine timer. The counter is incremented when a Paging message is sent to the eNodeB at the first transmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pspagingbypassquarantinetimersucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful PS Paging procedures that meet the following conditions, irrespective of the paging being an initial Paging message or the resending of the Paging message: - The PS Paging procedure is triggered by a DDN message. - The MME starts the PS Paging procedure by bypassing the paging quarantine timer. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from the UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pspagingrestartbasedonarpatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted PS Paging procedures that meet the following conditions: - The PS Paging procedure is triggered by a DDN message. - The MME restarts the PS Paging procedure by aborting the ongoing PS Paging procedure. The counter is incremented at the restart of the Paging procedure. Note: This counter is applicable only when MPS-classified ARP level is not configured.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pspagingrestartbasedonarpsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful PS Paging procedures that meet the following conditions, irrespective of the paging being an initial Paging message or the resending of the Paging message: - The PS Paging procedure is triggered by a DDN message. - The MME restarts the PS Paging procedure by aborting the ongoing PS Paging procedure. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from the UE is received. Note: This counter is applicable only when MPS-classified ARP level is not configured.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_publicwarningsystemdiscardedpagingmessage_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of S1-AP paging messages discarded during sending of the PWS-related signaling when the DiscardPagingDuringPWS parameter is set to true.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_repeatpagingtimerexpired_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed paging procedures with expired quarantine timer. The counter is incremented when the quarantine timer expires before receiving any Initial UE Message.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_repeatpagingtimerstarted_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed paging procedures that start a quarantine timer for paging.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_repeatpagingtimerstartedfirst_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed paging procedures that start a quarantine timer for the first time in a quarantine sequence.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1pagingmessages
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of paging messages sent by the #SGSN-MME# over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when a paging message is sent by the #SGSN-MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1release
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of S1 releases in the #MME#. Both eNodeB and MME initiated releases are counted. Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1releasembrtimeout
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of MME-initiated S1 Release procedures that are triggered due to timeout in waiting for the Modify Bearer Response message in the following procedures: - Service Request. - Control Plane Service Request. - S1/S11 bearer setup following a TAU procedure (for example, TAU with active flag or signaling active flag). - Connection Resume procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1releasepreemption
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to cause "Release due to Pre-Emption".
Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#, after receiving a UE Context Release Request or Handover Cancel from the eNodeB with cause "Release due to Pre-Emption".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1releaseradioconnectionlost
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost".
Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#, after receiving a UE Context Release Request or Handover Cancel from the eNodeB with cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1releasestophoretryattempts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of S1 releases initiated by the #MME# to prevent the source #eNodeB# from making repeated handover retry attempts in some extreme situations.
The measurement is now used for the Location Based IP Address Allocation feature only.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_s1releaseuserinactivity
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to cause "User Inactivity".
Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#, after receiving a UE Context Release Request from the eNodeB with cause "User Inactivity".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicereqlapiatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Service Requests sent from the low access priority UE to the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicereqlapirejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Service Requests from the low access priority UE when the NAS Level Mobility Mangement Congestion Control is activated.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicereqnascongestioncontrolrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Service Request due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicerequscdetached_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicerequscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicerequscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicerequestrejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Service Request procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when a Service Reject message is sent to the UE because all the APNs in the EPS Bearer Context stored for the UE are restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_smspagingatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MT# #SMS# paging procedures due to #MT# #SMS#, initiated at the #MME# over the S1-MME interface. The counter is incremented when an #SMS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #S-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #MT# #SMS# from an #MSC/VLR# is regarded as a new procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_smspagingsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to #MT# #SMS#, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to #SMS#, is successfully concluded.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsandpstowatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SRVCC CS and PS procedures from LTE to WCDMA. It is incremented when a Handover Required message with the SRVCC HO Indication IE indicating "CS and PS" is received from the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsandpstowcssuccpsfailed_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SRVCC CS and PS procedures from LTE to WCDMA where the CS part is successful but the PS part fails. This counter is incremented when a PS to CS Complete Notification is received from MSC and a Forward Relocation Response or Forward Relocation Complete Notification either times out or is received with cause code indicating failure reported by the SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsandpstowsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful SRVCC CS and PS procedures from LTE to WCDMA. It is incremented when both an SRVCC PS to CS Complete Notification message from the MSC and a Forward Relocation Complete Notification from the SGSN is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsonlytogatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SRVCC CS Only procedures to GSM in the MME. It is incremented when a Handover Required message with the SRVCC HO Indication IE indicating "CS only" is received from the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsonlytogsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful SRVCC CS only procedures to GSM in the MME. It is incremented each time an SRVCC CS only procedure is successfully concluded, at the reception of an SRVCC PS to CS Complete Notification message from the MSC server over the Sv interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsonlytowatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SRVCC CS Only procedures to WCDMA in the MME. It is incremented when a Handover Required message with the SRVCC HO Indication IE indicating 'CS only' is received from the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srvcccsonlytowsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful SRVCC CS only procedures to WCDMA in the MME. It is incremented each time an SRVCC CS only procedure is successfully concluded, at the reception of an SRVCC PS to CS Complete Notification message from the MSC server over the Sv interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succattach_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within this #MME# area. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an Attach Complete message.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succdetachmme
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #MME#-initiated #EPS# detach requests, node total. It is incremented when the #MME# receives an expected detach accept.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succenodeblistpaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on the latest visited eNodeB list, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of a paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request message or any other NAS message from the #UE# is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succfirstpspaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of #PS# paging procedures that are successful at the first paging message in the paging procedure. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succlastvisitedenodebpaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on LastVisitedENodeB, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succlastvisitedtapaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on LastVisistedTa, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succpspaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful #PS# paging procedures, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succtalistpaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on TaList, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_talamisconfigurationmscsupervision
vs_mm_tauinteratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated within this #MME# area. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_11_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_12_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_13_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_14_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with a cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_15_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_6_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Inter-MME TAU procedures over the S10 interface due to cause code 6. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Reject message with cause code 6 (Illegal ME).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_8_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Inter-MME TAU procedures over the S10 interface due to cause code 8. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Reject message with cause code 8 (Not authorized EPS and non-EPS service).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_9_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME# which resulted in cause code #9, "UE identity cannot be derived by the network".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauinterfail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Reject message is transmitted to the #UE#.
#Note: The number of successful attempts substracted from the total number of attempts does not equal the number of unsuccessful procedures due to discarded and resent messages. Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintersucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintersuccwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-MME TAU procedures, after which the UE is in the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintraatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated within this #MME# area. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.
All types of intra-MME #TAU# requests are counted, that is, both Intra-MME #TAU# and Periodic #TAU#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrafail_11_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrafail_12_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrafail_13_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrafail_14_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrafail_15_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrasucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Periodic and Intra-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauintrasuccwithoutpdn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-MME TAU procedures, after which the UE is in the EMM-REGISTERED state without PDN connection.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauperiodicatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Periodic TAU procedures initiated within this MME area. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tauperiodicsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Periodic TAU procedures initiated within this MME area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_unsuccattach_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #E-UTRAN# attach requests per MME This counter is increased whenever an Attach Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control.
Note: The number of successful attempts subtracted from the total number of attempts does not equal the number of unsuccessful attempts due to discarded messages, resent messages, and messages controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_unsuccattachcc27_28_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# Attach procedures per #MME# because of cause code 27 (Unknown or missing #APN#) and cause code 28 (Unknown #PDN# address or #PDN# type). The counter is incremented in the following scenarios: - The #MME# receives a Create Session Response message with cause code 78 (Missing or unknown #APN#) from the #SGW#. - The #MME# interrogates the #DNS# resolver and there is a failure, such as name error or undefined default #APN# of the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_unsuccattachcc32_33_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures per #MME# due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDN# Type is not supported or if the request is denied in the #MME# due to subscriber data restriction.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_unsuccservicereq_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S1 Service Request procedures in the MME. This counter is increased whenever an Service Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_updatelocationansfail_5001
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location Answer procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5001. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5001 (User unknown).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_updatelocationansfail_5004
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5004. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5004 (Roaming not allowed).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_updatelocationansfail_5420
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5420. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5420 (Unknown EPS subscription).

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_updatelocationansfail_5421
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5421. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5421 (RAT not allowed).

EntityDef.name: date_id
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: DATE_ID

EntityDef.name: granularity
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: GRANULARITY

EntityDef.name: moid
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: MOID

EntityDef.name: node
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: NODE NAME

EntityDef.name: ropendtime
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: ROP ENDTIME

EntityDef.name: utc_timestamp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: UTC TIMESTAMP

EntityDef.name: local_timestamp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: LOCAL TIMESTAMP

EntityDef.name: mm_attcombiintersgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates (inter-#SGSN#) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts.

EntityDef.name: mm_attcombiintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates (intra-SGSN) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_attgprsattach_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_attgprsdetachms_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_attgprsdetachsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures initiated by #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attimsicombiintersgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates with #IMSI# attach (inter-#SGSN#) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts.

EntityDef.name: mm_attimsicombiintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates with #IMSI# attach (intra-SGSN) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_attintersgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_attnormalintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates and #RA# updates acting as resume of a suspended #MS# are not counted. Resending from #MSs# is also counted. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_attpspagingprocgb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Gb interface. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# #PDU#, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with #IMSI# (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbractattachedsubra_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers per #RA# within this SGSN.
