#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_succcombiintersgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed combined #RA#/#LA# updates (inter-#SGSN#) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: mm_succcombiintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed combined #RA#/#LA# update (intra-SGSN) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_succfirstpspaginggb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful PS paging procedures that are successful at the first paging message in the paging procedure.

EntityDef.name: mm_succgprsattach_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_succgprsdetachsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #SGSN#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_succintersgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures in this #SGSN#. The counter is incremented when #RAU# Accept is transmitted.

EntityDef.name: mm_succintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_succnormalintrasgsnraupdate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates and #RA# updates acting as resume of a suspended #MS# are not counted. The counter is not stepped when resending a #RA# Update Accept message to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_succpspagingprocgb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Gb interface. The initial paging procedures as well as the repeated paging procedures are counted.

EntityDef.name: mm_attattachacceptnon3gppcompliant_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This is the name of the counter that gives, for attempted attach procedures, the number of 'Attach Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non 3GPP compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #GSM#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attauthciphreqnon3gppcompliant_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This is the name of the counter that gives, for attempted authentication and ciphering procedures, the number of 'Authentication and Ciphering Request' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #GSM#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attcancellochlrop_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted GPRS detaches initiated by the HLR within an SGSN. It is incremented when a Cancel Location message is received from the HLR with the cancelation type "subscription withdrawn". Resent Cancel Location messages from the HLR are also counted.

EntityDef.name: mm_attchangeoflocaltime_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Incremented when #SGSN# detects an attempt to change in offset and/or daylight savings time in #SGSNs# handling of #MS# local time.

EntityDef.name: mm_attdetachinactivesub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted detach of inactive subscribers procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_attintrasgsnraupdateuscdiscarded_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of attempted Intra-SGSN Routing Area Update procedures that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies a Intra-SGSN Routing Area Request message from the SGSN during a control period. Applies to GSM systems only.

EntityDef.name: mm_attrauacceptnon3gppcompliant_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This is the name of the counter that gives, for attempted routing area update procedures, the number of 'Routing Area Update Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #GSM#.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbractattachedsub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers within this #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers in the #SGSN-MME#. The gauge will then be incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication that the #SGSN-MME# is approaching the maximum number of attached subscribers. Offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #BSC#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrcamelsub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscriber within this #SGSN# area with #CAMEL# service. The counter is not incremented if the subscriber only have O-SMS CAMEL activated, and not GPRS CAMEL.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrhomesub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #GPRS# home subscribers located in the #SGSN# location register. The #GPRS# #MM# state of this subscriber is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in the same #GPRS# network are considered.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrmsisdnlesssub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of MSISDN-less subscribers that have registered at this SGSN (GSM). MSISDN-less subscribers are subscribers without the MSISDN at the HLR or HSS. The gauge is increased when an MSISDN-less subscriber successfully attaches to this SGSN. The gauge is decreased when an MSISDN-less subscriber is detached from this SGSN. The gauge can be also updated when inter-SGSN RAU, ISC RAU, or SGSN pool move is performed for an MSISDN-less subscriber.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrvisitingforeign_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of international roaming subscribers in the #SGSN#, where the #MCC# in the #IMSI# number is not part of the #PLMN#s supported by the #SGSN#. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. #Note: Home subscribers with different #MCC#s included in the #IMSI# number and accessing #RAI# are also counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrvisitingnatsub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of national roaming subscribers in the #SGSN#, where the #MCC# in the #IMSI# number is one of the #MCC#s of the #PLMN#s supported by the #SGSN#. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. #Note: Home subscribers with the same #MCC#s but different #MNC#s included in the #IMSI# number and accessing #RAI# are also counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc11_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc13_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this location area".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc14_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc15_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #15, "No suitable cells in location area".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc17_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc17redirectionind_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Attach procedures with the cause code #17 "Network Failure" and the SGSN provides Redirection Indication to the BSC in a MOCN constellation.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc22_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #22, "Congestion".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc6_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM attach procedures per SGSN due to cause code #6, "Illegal ME". It is incremented when the SGSN returns an Attach Reject message to the MS with cause code #6 or aborts the attach procedure due to an IMEISV check failure without sending the reject message.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc7_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #7, "GPRS Services not allowed".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc8_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #8, "GPRS and non GPRS services not allowed".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc96_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM attach procedures that return cause code #96, "Mandatory information element error".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcspscoord_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Attach procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccisraucspscoord_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-SGSN RAU procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnrau_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high inter routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful inter routing area requests due to cause code 9 (MS identity cannot be derived by the network), cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc10_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS# with cause code #10, Implicitly detached.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc13_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM inter-SGSN RAU procedures that return cause code 13, "Roaming not allowed in this location area".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc14_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN RAU procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc15_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the MS with cause code #15, No Suitable Cells In Location Area.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc17_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc9_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures that return cause code #9, "MS identity cannot be derived by the network".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucspscoord_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Intra-SGSN RAU procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation. The Intra-SGSN ISC procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnrau_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high intra routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful intra routing area updates due to cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucc14_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucc15_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #15, "No Suitable Cells In Location Area". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucc17_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccraucc17redirectionind_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful RAU procedures with the cause code #17 "Network Failure" and the SGSN provides Redirection Indication to the BSC in a MOCN constellation. Intra-RAU, inter-RAU and ISC are all counted.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrdetachedinactivesub_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of detached inactive subscribers within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attlastvisitedcellpaging_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted paging procedures based on last visited cell. This counter is incremented when a Paging Request message is sent to the cell the UE has just visited. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LastVisitedCell within a paging profile. Retransmission of Paging Request messages based on last visited cell is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attrapaging_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted paging procedures based on the RA a UE has registered. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the whole RA. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of RA within a paging profile. Retransmission of Paging Request based on RA is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachuscdiscarded_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The number of Attach Request messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and discarded during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_interrauuscdiscarded_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The number of Inter-SGSN RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrattachedpsm_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #UEs# currently in Power Saving Mode (PSM). The gauge is incremented when a #UE# enters PSM, that is when the active timer expires and the implicit detach timer is started. The gauge is decremented when a #UE# leaves PSM, that is when any kind of signaling from the #UE# is received or when the #UE# is implicitly detached.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_ptmsireallocation_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of P-TMSI reallocation procedures initiated by the SGSN. The counter is incremented when a P-TMSI Reallocation Command message is sent to the MS. The resending of the P-TMSI Reallocation Command message is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_raufailnoipv4_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful RAU procedures due to no IPv4 address in GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane in the (SGSN) Context Response in WCDMA access. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: To find out the problems, check the MME/SGSN from which the UE comes. The UE may activate PDP context/EPS bearer with only IPv6 address in the GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succlastvisitedcellpaging_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on LastVisitedCell, irrespective of the paging being an initial Paging Request message or the resending of a Paging Request message. The counter is incremented when an LLC Frame from MS is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_succrapaging_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on RA, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when an LLC Frame from MS is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_purgemshlratt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Gr Purge MS procedures in the SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_purgemshlrsucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Gr Purge MS procedures in the SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tadsrequesthlratt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted T-ADS requests from HLR. It is incremented when a Provide Subscriber Information message with the Requested Info IE indicating T-ADS is received from HLR.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_purgeuehssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted S6a/S6d Purge UE procedures in the SGSN-MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_purgeuehsssucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful S6a/S6d Purge UE procedures in the SGSN-MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tadsrequesthssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted T-ADS requests from HSS. It is incremented when an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating T-ADS Data Request is received from HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_ueswithlocationnotconfirmed
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UEs whose location is currently not updated towards the HSS/HLR. This can happen either after HSS/HLR reset, or when attach throttling is activated and a Geo-Redundant failover happens or during and after a pool move.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_updlochssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted S6a/S6d Update Location procedures in the SGSN-MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_updlochsssucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful S6a/S6d Update Location procedures in the SGSN-MME.

EntityDef.name: mm_attgprsattach_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_attgprsdetachms_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_attgprsdetachsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures initiated by #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attintersgsnraupdate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attintrasgsnraupdate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_attnormalintrasgsnraupdate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates are not counted. Resending from #MSs# is also counted. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_attpspaginghpaprociu
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted HPA paging procedures initiated at the SGSN over the Iu interface. The counter is incremented when an HPA paging procedure is started, that is, at the transmission of the first HPA Paging Request message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more Paging Request messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by Paging Request messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of Paging Request messages, triggered by a new DL PDU, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with IMSI (due to an abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

EntityDef.name: mm_attpspagingprociu
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PS paging procedures initiated at the SGSN over the Iu interface. The counter is incremented when a PS paging procedure is started, that is, at the transmission of the first Paging Request message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more Paging Request messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by Paging Request messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of Paging Request messages, triggered by a new DL PDU, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with IMSI (due to an abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbractattachedsubra_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers per #RA# within this #SGSN#.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_succfirstpspaginghpaiu
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful HPA paging procedures that are successful at the first Paging Request message in the paging procedure.

EntityDef.name: mm_succfirstpspagingiu
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #PS# paging procedures that are successful at the first Paging Request message in the paging procedure.

EntityDef.name: mm_succgprsattach_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_succgprsdetachsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #SGSN#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: mm_succintersgsnraupdate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures in this #SGSN#. The counter is incremented when #RAU# Accept is transmitted.

EntityDef.name: mm_succintrasgsnraupdate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_succnormalintrasgsnraupdate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates are not counted. The counter is not stepped when resending #RA# Update Accept message to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_succpspaginghpaprociu
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of all successful HPA paging procedures initiated at the SGSN over the Iu interface.

EntityDef.name: mm_succpspagingprociu
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of all successful #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Iu interface.

EntityDef.name: mm_attattachacceptnon3gppcompliant_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This is the name of the counter that gives, for attempted attach procedures, the number of 'Attach Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #WCDMA#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attauthciphreqnon3gppcompliant_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This is the name of the counter that gives, for attempted authentication and ciphering procedures, the number of 'Authentication and Ciphering Request' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #WCDMA#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attcancellochlrop_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted GPRS detaches initiated by the HLR within an SGSN. It is incremented when a Cancel Location message is received from the HLR with the cancelation type "subscription withdrawn". Resent Cancel Location messages from the HLR are also counted.

EntityDef.name: mm_attchangeoflocaltime_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Incremented when #SGSN# detects an attempt to change in offset and/or daylight savings time in #SGSNs# handling of #MS# local time.

EntityDef.name: mm_attdetachinactivesub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted detach of inactive subscribers procedures within this SGSN area.

EntityDef.name: mm_attintrasgsnraupdateuscdiscarded_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of attempted Intra-SGSN Routing Area Update procedures that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies a Intra-SGSN Routing Area Request message from the SGSN during a control period. Applies to WCDMA systems only.

EntityDef.name: mm_attrauacceptnon3gppcompliant_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This is the name of the counter that gives, for attempted routing area update procedures, the number of 'Routing Area Update Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #WCDMA#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attservicereqdata_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures of data type in the #SGSN#. It is incremented when Service request, with service type data, is received from the MS.

EntityDef.name: mm_attservicerequest_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures of data, signaling, or paging response type, in the #SGSN#. It is incremented when a Service Request is received from the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: mm_attservicerequestuscdiscarded_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of attempted Service Request procedures of data, signaling, and paging response types that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies a Service Request message from a UE during a control period.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbractattachedsub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers within this #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers in the #SGSN-MME#. The gauge will then be incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication that the #SGSN-MME# is approaching the maximum number of attached subscribers. Offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #RNC#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrcamelsub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscriber within this #SGSN# area with #CAMEL# service.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrhomesub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #GPRS# home subscribers located in the #SGSN# location register. The #GPRS# #MM# state of this subscriber is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in the same #GPRS# network are considered.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrmsisdnlesssub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of MSISDN-less subscribers that have registered at this SGSN (WCDMA). MSISDN-less subscribers are subscribers without the MSISDN at the HLR or HSS. The gauge is increased when an MSISDN-less subscriber successfully attaches to this SGSN. The gauge is decreased when an MSISDN-less subscriber is detached from this SGSN. The gauge can be also updated when inter-SGSN RAU, ISC RAU, or SGSN pool move is performed for an MSISDN-less subscriber.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrsubpmmconnected
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of subscribers in PMM-CONNECTED state.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrvisitingforeign_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of international roaming subscribers in the #SGSN#, where the #MCC# in the #IMSI# number is not part of the #PLMN#s supported by the #SGSN#. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. #Note: Home subscribers with different #MCC#s included in the #IMSI# number and accessing #RAI# are also counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrvisitingnatsub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of national roaming subscribers in the #SGSN#, where the #MCC# in the #IMSI# number is one of the #MCC#s of the #PLMN#s supported by the #SGSN#. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. #Note: Home subscribers with the same #MCC#s but different #MNC#s included in the #IMSI# number and accessing #RAI# are also counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc11_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc13_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this location area".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc14_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc15_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #15, "No suitable cells in location area".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc17_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc22_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #22, "Congestion".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc6_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM attach procedures per SGSN due to cause code #6, "Illegal ME". It is incremented when the SGSN returns an Attach Reject message to the MS with cause code #6 or aborts the attach procedure due to an IMEISV check failure without sending the reject message.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc7_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #7, "GPRS Services not allowed".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcc8_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that return cause code #8, "GPRS and non GPRS services not allowed".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccattachcspscoord_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attach procedures being rejected due to coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a #MOCN# constellation.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccisraucspscoord_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of inter-#SGSN# RAU procedures being rejected due to coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a #MOCN# constellation.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnrau_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#.
This is an indication of high inter routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful inter routing area requests due to cause code 9 (MS identity cannot be derived by the network), cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc10_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS# with cause code #10, Implicitly detached.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc13_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM inter-SGSN RAU procedures that return cause code 13, "Roaming not allowed in this location area".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc14_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc15_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS# with cause code #15, No Suitable Cells In Location Area.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc17_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSNJ #RAU# procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintersgsnraucc9_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures that return cause code #9, "MS identity cannot be derived by the network".

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucspscoord_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN #RAU# procedures being rejected due to the coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a #MOCN# constellation. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnrau_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high intra routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful intra routing area updates due to cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucc14_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucc15_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #15, "No Suitable Cells In Location Area". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccintrasgsnraucc17_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: mm_unsuccservicereq_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Service Request procedures in the #SGSN#. This counter is increased whenever an Service Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control.

EntityDef.name: mm_nbrdetachedinactivesub_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of detached inactive subscribers within this SGSN area.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachuscdiscarded_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The number of Attach Request messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and discarded during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_attachuscrejected_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_hsshlrfallbatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement is part of the "HSS/HLR-selection based on EPC Capability" function.
It provides the number of attempted fallbacks to #HLR# after a failed #HSS# answer.
Trigger: the initiation of a Send Authentication Info-, or a Send Parameters-, or an Update #GPRS# Location-service to the #HLR# after a failed #HSS# answer.
Note: This measurement is only applicable for the SGSN-MME with single W access or LW dual access.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_hsshlrfallbsucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement is part of the "HSS/HLR-selection based on EPC Capability" function.
It provides the number of successful transactions to #HLR# after a previous #HSS#/#HLR#-fallback.
Trigger: the successful completion of a Send Authentication Info-, or a Send Parameters-, or an Update #GPRS# Location-service to the #HLR# after a failed #HSS# answer.
Note: This measurement is only applicable for the SGSN-MME with single W access or LW dual access.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_interrauuscdiscarded_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The number of Inter-SGSN RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_interrauuscrejected_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Inter-SGSN RAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Inter-SGSN RAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrasgsnraupdateuscdetached_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Intra-SGSN RAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Intra-SGSN RAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_intrasgsnraupdateuscrejected_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Intra-SGSN RAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Intra-SGSN RAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_iurelease
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Iu releases in the #SGSN#. Both #RNC# and SGSN initiated releases are counted. Trigger: Sending Iu Release Command to the RNC.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_iureleaseradioconnectionlost
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of RNC-initiated Iu releases due to cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost".
Trigger: Sending Iu Release Command to the RNC after receiving an Iu Release Request with cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_iureleaseuserinactivity
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of RNC-initiated Iu releases due to cause "User Inactivity".
Trigger: Sending Iu Release Command to the RNC after receiving an Iu Release Request with cause "User Inactivity".

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportchangeofservicearea_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Report messages with the "Change of Service Area" request type and an SAI received by the SGSN. This counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a RANAP Location Report message with the "Change of Service Area" request type and an SAI from the RNC over the Iu interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportcontrolchangeofservicearea_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Reporting Control messages with the "Change of Service Area" request type sent by the SGSN. This counter is incremented when the SGSN sends a RANAP Location Reporting Control message with the "Change of Service Area" request type to the RNC over the Iu interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationreportfailurechangeofservicearea_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Location Report messages with the "Change of Service Area" request type, and a failure cause or no SAI. This counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a RANAP Location Report message with the "Change of Service Area" request type from the RNC over the Iu interface and the message has a failure cause or does not have an SAI.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrnwsharingnonsuppue_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers which are network sharing non-supporting UEs within the MOCN enabled #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers which are network sharing non-supporting UEs in the MOCN enabled #SGSN-MME#. The gauge is incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nbrnwsharingsuppue_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers which are network sharing supporting UEs within the MOCN enabled SGSN-MME area.
Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers which are network sharing supporting UEs in the MOCN enabled SGSN-MME. The gauge is incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-SGSN RA Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_ptmsireallocation_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of P-TMSI reallocation procedures initiated by the SGSN. The counter is incremented when a P-TMSI Reallocation Command message is sent to the MS. The resending of the P-TMSI Reallocation Command message is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_raufailnoipv4_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful RAU procedures due to no IPv4 address in GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane in the (SGSN) Context Response in WCDMA access. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: To find out the problems, check the MME/SGSN from which the UE comes. The UE may activate PDP context/EPS bearer with only IPv6 address in the GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicerequestuscdetached_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_servicerequestuscrejected_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_srnscontextrequest
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SRNS Context Transfers in the #SGSN#. This counter is increased when the #SGSN# sends an SRNS Context Request to the #RNC#.

EntityDef.name: attcombiattach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempt of combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resendings from #MSs# are counted.

EntityDef.name: attcombidetachms
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# detach procedures #MS#-initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resendings from #MSs# are counted.

EntityDef.name: attgprsattach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. Resendings from #MSs# are also counted.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: attgprsattachvisitor
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures, within this #SGSN# area, initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers . Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration. Resendings from #MSs# are not counted.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: attgprsdetachms
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area. Resendings from #MSs# are also counted.

EntityDef.name: attgprsdetachsgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures initiated by #SGSN#. The counter is incremented when sending Detach Request to an #MS#. The counter is not incremented when resending Detach Request to the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: attimsidetachms
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #IMSI# detach procedures #MS#-initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resendings from #MSs# are counted.

EntityDef.name: attintersgsnraupdate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#, where the old #RA# is served by another #SGSN#. Both sendings and resending from #MSs# are also counted.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: attintersgsnraupdatevisitor
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers within this #SGSN#, where the old #RA# is served by another #SGSN#. Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration. Resendings from #MSs# are not counted.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: attintrasgsnraupdate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resending from #MSs# are counted. All types of intra-SGSN #RA# Update requests are counted: normal #RA# update, periodic #RA# update and #RA# update acting as resume of a suspended #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: attpacketswitchingpaging
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the aggregation of the MM.AttPsPagingProcGb measurement types.

EntityDef.name: discardedattachmserror
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The discardedAttachMsError counter is incremented when there is a rejected attach because the #MS# has wrong #TLLI#. There is an #IMSI# attach on non-random #TLLI#.

EntityDef.name: discardedcombiattach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded combined attach requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements. For information about the possible reject causes, refer to the Cause Codes and Events document.

EntityDef.name: discardedcombiraupdate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded combined routing area update requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements.

EntityDef.name: discardeddetach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded detach requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements.

EntityDef.name: discardedgprsattach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded attach requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements. #GPRS# attach and GPRS attach with #IMSI# already attached are included.

EntityDef.name: discardedpayloadpacket
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded payload #PDUs# on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements.

EntityDef.name: discardedraupdate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded routing area update requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements

EntityDef.name: gprsmmsgsnpagingprocedures
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Gb interface. The counter is incremented when a paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The #PS# paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# #PDU#, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with #IMSI# (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure. This measurement counts both #CS# and #PS# paging procedures. Note that there is no repetition for #CS# paging, hence each #CS# paging message is counted as one procedure.

EntityDef.name: gprsmmsgsnrejectedbyadmissioncontrol
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Number of Attach or Inter-#SGSN# #RA#-update requests that were rejected by admission control. The request is rejected and fault code 22 is sent to the #MS#, indicating congestion. The admission control reject is caused by maximum #SAU# limit reached.

EntityDef.name: gprsmmsgsnsuccessfulpagingprocedures
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the aggregation of the MM.SuccPsPagingProcGb measurement types.

EntityDef.name: gprsmmsgsnunsuccessfulattachrequests
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful attach request per #SGSN-MME#, that is, whenever an attach reject message is sent.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high attach failure rates, typically caused by a decision not to allow #GPRS# usage for some subscriber categories. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful attaches due to cause code 7 (#GPRS# not allowed), cause code 8 (#GPRS# services and non-#GPRS# services not allowed) and cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#). If the attach failure rate remains on a high failure rate, continue the troubleshooting by checking the #SS7# network.

EntityDef.name: nbrofsubready
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of subscribers in READY state within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: nbrofsubstandby
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of subscribers in STANDBY state within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: succcombiattach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed of Combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. The counter is not incremented when resending Attach Accept to the #MS#. If the #IMSI# (CS) Attach failed but the #GPRS# Attach was successful, no counters are incremented.

EntityDef.name: succgprsattach
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area. The counter is not incremented when resending Attach Accept to the #MS#. If an Attach Request indicating Combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# Attach was received and the #IMSI# (CS) Attach failed but the #GPRS# Attach was successful, the counter is not incremented.

EntityDef.name: succgprsattachvisitor
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area, initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers. Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration. If the SGSN resends an Attach Accept message to the #MS#, the counter is not incremented. If the SGSN receives an Attach Request message indicating Combined #GPRS# or #IMSI# Attach and the #IMSI# (CS) Attach did fail whereas the #GPRS# Attach was successful, the counter is not incremented.

EntityDef.name: succgprsdetachsgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #GPRS# detach procedures #SGSN#-initiated within this #SGSN# area. The procedure is not considered successful if Detach Accept is not received, even though the #MS# is detached in the network.

EntityDef.name: succintersgsnraupdate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures in this #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: succintersgsnraupdatevisitor
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers within this #SGSN# area. Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration.

EntityDef.name: succintrasgsnraupdate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The counter is not stepped when resending #RA# update "accept". All types of intra-SGSN #RA# update requests are counted: normal #RA# update, periodic #RA# update and #RA# update acting as resume of a suspended #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

EntityDef.name: unsuccpacketswitchingpaging
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful packet switched paging procedures over the Gb interface within this #SGSN-MME# area, that is, packet switching paging procedures that are re-started when the previous attempt has timed out. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure has failed, that is, at timeout after transmission of the last paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# PDU, is regarded as a new procedure. Note that the total number of attempts minus successful attempts is not the same as unsuccessful due to discarded messages and re-sendings of messages.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high paging failure rates, typically caused by lack of radio coverage. Continue the troubleshooting in the radio network.

EntityDef.name: subscribersintransitionalstate
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
The gauge shows the number of subscribers in transitional state, that is, the number of users that are in the middle of Attach/Detach or #PDP# context Activation/Deactivation procedures.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of a high number of subscribers in a transitional state, and that the signaling procedures can not be completed in a reasonable time. This can be caused by overload. Check the networks and external interfaces for congestion. For more information, see Troubleshooting.

EntityDef.name: unsuccgprsattachumts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful attach request per #SGSN#. This counter is increased whenever an Attach Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control.
Note: The number of successful attempts subtracted from the total number of attempts does not equal the number of unsuccessful attempts due to discarded messages, resent messages, and messages controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature.

EntityDef.name: unsuccpacketswitchingpaginghpaumts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful HPA paging procedures over the Iu interface per SGSN. The counter is incremented when an HPA paging procedure has failed. That is, at timeout after transmission of the last HPA Paging Request message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more Paging Request messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by Paging Request messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of Paging Request messages, triggered by a new DL PDU, is regarded as a new procedure. Note that the total number of attempted paging procedures minus the total number of successful paging procedures is not the same as the total number of unsuccessful paging procedures. This is because discarded and retransmitted paging messages are not counted as unsuccessful paging procedures.

EntityDef.name: unsuccpacketswitchingpagingumts
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful packet switched paging procedures over the Iu interface per SGSN. That is, packet switching paging procedures that are re-started when the previous attempt has timed out. The counter is incremented when a PS paging procedure has failed. That is, at timeout after transmission of the last Paging Request message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more Paging Request messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by Paging Request messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of Paging Request messages, triggered by a new DL PDU, is regarded as a new procedure. Note that the total number of attempted paging procedures minus the total number of successful paging procedures is not the same as the total number of unsuccessful paging procedures. This is because discarded and retransmitted paging messages are not counted as unsuccessful paging procedures.

EntityDef.name: reloc_attintersgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC. The number of attempted Inter-SGSN Relocation from S4-SGSN to Gn-SGSN is also counted.

EntityDef.name: reloc_attintersgsnnew
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #SRNS# Relocation procedures and inter #SGSN#/#MME# #IRAT# handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access counted in the new #SGSN#. The counter is incremented when the new #SGSN# receives an #SRNS# "Forward Relocation Request" message from the old #SGSN# or old #MME#. #Note: The Gn-#SGSN# as target side does not have enough information to decide if the source side is #SGSN# or #MME# during inter node #HO# from #GTPv1# Forward Relocation Request. Therefore, the Gn-#SGSN# uses RELOC.AttInterSGSNNew instead of VS.IRATHO.LteAttInc.U for all inter #HO# from #SGSN# or #MME#.Note#

EntityDef.name: reloc_attintersgsnnews16
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the new SGSN. The counter is incremented when the new SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Request" message from the old SGSN.

EntityDef.name: reloc_attintersgsnolds16
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC and the target RA is served by a new SGSN.

EntityDef.name: reloc_attintrasgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC.

EntityDef.name: reloc_attintrasgsns16
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC and the target RA is served by the same SGSN.

EntityDef.name: reloc_failintersgsnint
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the RNC and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons or when the old SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Response" message but not all of the needed RABs are allocated in the new SGSN. The number of failed Inter-SGSN Relocation from S4-SGSN to Gn-SGSN is also counted. The counter is not incremented when old S4-SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Response" message but not all of the needed RABs are allocated in the new Gn-SGSN.

EntityDef.name: reloc_failintersgsns16int
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Inter SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures for a UE using S4 mode counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC, the target RA is served by a new SGSN, and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons.

EntityDef.name: reloc_failintrasgsnint
reloc_failintrasgsns16int
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Intra SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures for a UE using S4 mode. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC, the target RA is served by the same SGSN, and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons.

EntityDef.name: reloc_succintersgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Complete" message from the new SGSN. The number of successful Inter-SGSN Relocation from S4-SGSN to Gn-SGSN is also counted.

EntityDef.name: reloc_succintersgsnnew
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful inter-#SGSN# #SRNS# Relocation procedures and inter #SGSN#/#MME# #IRAT# handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter is incremented when the new #SGSN# receives a "Forward Relocation Complete Acknowledge" message from the old #SGSN# or old #MME#, or the new #SGSN# fails to receive the "Forward Relocation Complete Acknowledge" message due to #GTP# message timeout after N3 timeouts and resendings. #Note: The Gn-#SGSN# as target side does not have enough information to decide if the source side is #SGSN# or #MME# during inter node #HO# from #GTPv1# Forward Relocation Request. Therefore, the Gn-#SGSN# uses RELOC.SuccInterSGSNNew instead of VS.IRATHO.LteSuccInc.U for all inter #HO# from #SGSN# or #MME#.Note#

EntityDef.name: reloc_succintersgsnnews16
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the new SGSN. The counter is incremented when the new SGSN receives a "Relocation Complete" message from the target RNC.

EntityDef.name: reloc_succintersgsnolds16
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Complete Notification" message from the new SGSN.

EntityDef.name: reloc_succintrasgsn
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures and intra-SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a "Relocation Complete" message from the target RNC.

EntityDef.name: reloc_succintrasgsns16
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a "Relocation Complete" message from the target RNC.

EntityDef.name: ospfareabdrrtrcount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of area border routers reachable within this area. This number is initially zero, and is calculated in each #SPF# pass.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This gauge can only increase as a result of network reconfiguration. No actions are recommended.

EntityDef.name: ospfarealsacount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of #LSA#s in this area's link-state database, excluding #AS# external #LSA#s.
If OSPF NSSA is used within the area this counter also includes Type 7 #LSA#s. In this case, the supervised threshold could also need to be increased.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Investigate why that many #LSA#s exist. The network might need to be redesigned. Consider using OSPF NSSA to reduce the number of #LSA#s.

EntityDef.name: ospfasbdrrtrcount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of autonomous system border routers reachable within this area. This number is initially zero, and is calculated in each #SPF# pass.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This gauge can only increase as a result of network reconfiguration. No actions are recommended.

EntityDef.name: ospfspfruns
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link-state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.

EntityDef.name: ospfexternlsacount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of external (LS type 5) #LSA#s in the link-state database. The #SGSN-MME# allows a maximum of 8000 #LSA#s. Exceeding this limit is at the risk of the operator.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Investigate why so many external #LSA#s exist and what entity in the network that announces them. The network might need to be redesigned. If OSPF NSSA is not used within the area, consider using it to reduce the number of external #LSA#s.

EntityDef.name: ospfrxnewlsas
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #LSAs# received determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated #LSAs#.
