EntityDef.name: sctpabortreqsent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user requested the #SCTP# to close an association to a remote endpoint by sending the #SCTP# Abort Request primitive.

EntityDef.name: sctpassocreestablishmentatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SCTP association reestablishment attempts on the S1-MME and SBc interfaces. The number of reestablishment attempts are calculated per SctpUserId, that is, per interface. Also see counters sctpAssocReestablishmentSuccLocal and sctpAssocReestablishmentSuccRemote.

EntityDef.name: sctpassocreestablishmentsucclocal
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful SCTP association reestablishment attempts on the S1-MME and SBc interfaces with the MME as the source of the establishment of the SCTP association. The number of successful reestablishment attempts are calculated per SctpUserId, that is, per interface. Also see counters sctpAssocReestablishmentSuccRemote and sctpAssocReestablishmentAtt.

EntityDef.name: sctpassocreestablishmentsuccremote
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful SCTP association reestablishment attempts on the S1-MME and SBc interfaces with the remote node, eNodeB or CBC, as the source of the establishment of the SCTP association. This case occurs when both SGSN-MME and the remote node tries to reestablish the association, and as SGSN-MME on the S1-MME and SBc interfaces acts as server, the SCTP association established from the remote node will be preferred. The number of successful reestablishment attempts are calculated per SctpUserId, that is, per interface. Also see counters sctpAssocReestablishmentSuccLocal and sctpAssocReestablishmentAtt.

EntityDef.name: sctpassocrestartindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Restart Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# has detected that the remote endpoint restarted the association.

EntityDef.name: sctpassociateconfreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Confirmation primitive has been received from #SCTP# to confirm that the #SCTP# tried to establish the association earlier requested by the #SCTP# user.

EntityDef.name: sctpassociatereqsent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user tried to establish an association by sending the #SCTP# Association Request primitive.

EntityDef.name: sctpcommerrorindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Error Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# received an error chunk from its remote endpoint and decided to notify the #SCTP# user.

EntityDef.name: sctpcommlostindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Lost Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to inform when the #SCTP# lost communication with an endpoint completely or detected an abort or a shutdown operation from the remote endpoint.

EntityDef.name: sctpcommupindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Up Indication primitive is received by the #SCTP# user to indicate when the #SCTP# became ready to send or receive #SCTP# User messages, or when a lost communication to a remote endpoint was restored.

EntityDef.name: sctpcongestionindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Congestion Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the remote endpoint is inaccessible due to failure or congestion. #SCTP# user traffic cannot be sent to this remote endpoint for the moment.

EntityDef.name: sctperrresultreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user failed to send a primitive due to various #SCTP# reasons. The counter is not incremented for the reason of high CPU load. Primitives that are blocked due to high CPU load have the counter ctpErrResultWouldBlockReceived incremented.

EntityDef.name: sctperrresultwouldblockreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user failed to send a primitive due to a blocked #SCTP#. The #SCTP# is blocked due to high load.

EntityDef.name: sctpmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #SCTP# user messages received from the remote endpoint.

EntityDef.name: sctpmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #SCTP# user messages sent to the remote endpoint.

EntityDef.name: sctpolpabortexistingassoc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times an existing #SCTP# association is aborted due to high CPU load.

EntityDef.name: sctpolpabortnewassoc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times a newly established #SCTP# association is aborted due to high CPU load.

EntityDef.name: sctpsendfailureindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Failure Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# has encountered a problem when trying to send a primitive, earlier requested by the #SCTP# user.

EntityDef.name: sctpsetulpkeyatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user tried to set the #ulpKey# parameter for one #SCTP# association by sending the #SCTP# Set ULP Key primitive.

EntityDef.name: sctpsetulpkeyfail
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user failed to set the #ulpKey# parameter for one #SCTP# association because sending the #SCTP# Set ULP Key primitive failed.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of the ignored SGsAP Paging Request messages indicating CS call from the MSC over the SGs interface, because either the UE is an SMS-only device or the UE is given the SMS-only capability by the MME. This counter is incremented each time when the MME receives the SGsAP Paging Request messages indicating CS call from MSC but does not respond to the MSC because either the UE is an SMS-only device or the UE is given the SMS-only capability by the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgs_downlinkunitdata_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Downlink Unitdata messages sent from the #MSC/VLR# to the #MME# on the SGs interface. This counter is incremented each time a Downlink Unitdata messages is received from an #MSC/VLR#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgs_mocsfbindication_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SGsAP-MO-CSFB-INDICATION messages on the SGs interface. This counter is incremented each time an SGsAP-MO-CSFB-INDICATION message is sent to an MSC/VLR.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgs_pagingcsrestoration_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SGs Paging messages with "CS Restoration Indicator" received over the SGs interface. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives an SGs Paging message with "CS Restoration Indicator" over the SGs interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgs_pagingreq_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SGsAP Paging Request received over the SGs interface. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives an SGsAP Paging Request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgs_uplinkunitdata_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Uplink Unitdata messages sent to the #MSC/VLR# from the #MME# on the SGs interface. This counter is incremented each time an Uplink Unitdata messages is sent to an #MSC/VLR#.

EntityDef.name: uplinksndcpnpdureceived

EntityDef.name: uplinksndcpnpdusentv42bisdecomp

EntityDef.name: uplinksndcpoctetreceivedmode
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of octets in incoming #N-PDUs# received by the #SNDCP# layer. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).

EntityDef.name: uplinksndcpoctetsentv42bisdecomp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of octets in incoming #N-PDUs# received and decompressed by the #SNDCP# layer. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspacackmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPAC# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPAC# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspacackmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPAC# message by sending an #ASPAC# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspacmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #ASPAC# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request for #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Inactive to state Active.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspacmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Process (SP) to move from state Inactive to state Active by sending the #ASPAC# message.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspdnackmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPDN# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPDN# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspdnackmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPDN# message by sending an #ASPDN# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspdnmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #ASPDN# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request for #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Inactive to state Down.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspdnmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Processor to move from state Inactive to state Down by sending the #ASPDN# message.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspiaackmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPIA# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPIA# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspiaackmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPIA# message by sending an #ASPIA# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspiamessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #ASPIA# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request for #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Active to state Inactive.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspiamessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Process to move from state Active to state Inactive by sending the #ASPIA# message.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspupackmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPUP# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPUP# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspupackmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPUP# message by sending an #ASPUP# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspupmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #ASPUP# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request to the #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Down to state Inactive.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaaspupmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Process to move from state Down to state Inactive by sending the #ASPUP# message.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadaudmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAUD# message has been received from #ASP# to request #SS7# destination audit for the #SG#/#SGP#. #SGSN# does not support being an #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadaudmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAUD# message has been sent from #M3UA# #ASP# to request #SS7# destination audit for an #SG#/#SGP#.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadavamessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAVA# message has been received from the Remote #SGP# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are available.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadavamessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAVA# message has been sent from #M3UA# #ASP# or IP Signaling Process in response to a #DAUD# message. #SGSN# does not support being #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadrstmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DRST# message has been received from the #SG# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are restricted.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadrstmessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DRST# message has been sent from #SG# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are now restricted. #SGSN# does not support acting as an #SGP#, so the counter should always be 0.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadunamessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUNA# message has been received from the Remote #SGP# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are unreachable.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadunamessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUNA# message has been sent from #M3UA# #ASP#/#IPSP# in response to a #DAUD# message. #SGSN# does not support being #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadupumessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUPU# message has been received from the Remote #SGP# to inform that a remote peer #MTP-L3# User Part at an #SS7# node is unavailable.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uadupumessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUPU# message has been sent from an #SGP# to inform that a remote peer #MTP-L3# User Part at an #SS7# node is unavailable. #SGSN# does not support being #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaerrormessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# Error message has been received from the Remote Signaling Process to inform #M3UA# of an error event associated with an incoming message (for example Invalid Parameter Value).

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uaerrormessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# Error message has been sent from #M3UA# to inform the Remote Signaling Process of an error event associated with an incoming message (for example Invalid Parameter Value).

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uanotifymessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #NTFY# message has been received from the Remote #SGP#/#IPSP# to inform that the state of the remote #AS# has been changed.

EntityDef.name: ss7m3uanotifymessagesent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #NTFY# message has been sent from #M3UA#/#IPSP# to inform all remote #ASPs# that the state of this #AS# has changed.

EntityDef.name: ss7messagereceivedfromremotesp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #MSUs# received from remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 900 sec.

EntityDef.name: ss7messagesenttoremotesp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #MSUs# sent to remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 900 sec.

EntityDef.name: ss7octetsreceivedfromremotesp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of KB received from remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 3600 sec.

EntityDef.name: ss7octetssenttoremotesp
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of KB sent to remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 3600 sec.

EntityDef.name: ss7remotespavlforup
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Remote Signaling Process has become available for User Part traffic (association moved to active state).

EntityDef.name: ss7remotespunavlforup
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Remote Signaling Process has become unavailable for User Part traffic (association moved from active state).

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpabortreqsent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested that the #SCTP# should close an association by sending the #SCTP# Abort Request message.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpassocrestartindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Restart Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# has detected that the remote peer restarted the association.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpassociateconfreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Confirmation message has been received from #SCTP# to confirm that the #SCTP# tried to establish the association earlier requested by M3UA.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpassociatereqsent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# tried to establish an association by sending the #SCTP# Association Request message.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpcommerrorindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Error Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that #SCTP# received an Error chunk from its peer and decided to notify #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpcommlostindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Lost Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to inform when #SCTP# lost communication with an endpoint completely or detected an abort or a shutdown operation from the endpoint.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpcommupreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Up Indication message is received by #M3UA# to indicate when #SCTP# became ready to send or receive #M3UA# messages, or when a lost communication to an endpoint was restored.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpcongestionindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Congestion Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that the remote Signaling Process is inaccessible due to failure or congestion. #M3UA# traffic cannot be sent to this destination for the moment.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpfailureindreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Failure Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that #SCTP# has encountered a problem when trying to send a message, earlier requested by #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpshutdownconfreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Shutdown Confirmation message has been received from #SCTP# to confirm that the shutdown process, earlier requested from #M3UA#, has started successfully or not.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpshutdownreqsent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# tried to close an association by sending the #SCTP# Shutdown Request message.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpstatusconfreceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Status Confirmation message has been received from #SCTP# to inform #M3UA# about the current status of the endpoint, requested earlier by #M3UA#.

EntityDef.name: ss7sctpstatusreqsent
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested that the #SCTP# should return the current status of the endpoint by sending the #SCTP# Status Request message.

EntityDef.name: ss7msudiscarderror
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: The #MSU# is discarded due to routing data error. The message could not be routed and was therefore discarded.;The standard routing label contains the destination and originating point of the message, along with the signaling link selection (used for selecting which signaling link to use). One of these fields was invalid in the message received from the user part.;Inspection of the log file may show the content of the invalid message field, received from the MTP-L3 user, and clarify the cause of the error.

EntityDef.name: ss7messagediscardedopcscreening
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of discarded #MSU# packets received. The packets are discarded by the #OPC# screening when the received OPC is not accepted. The ss7M3MSUDiscardedOPCScreening event includes both the received #OPC# and the adjacent #DPC#.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of sent Connection Request messages. It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

EntityDef.name: ss7messageorigdt1
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Data Form 1 messages sent (Connection Oriented data). It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

EntityDef.name: ss7messageorigrlsd
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Released messages sent. It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

EntityDef.name: ss7messagetermcr
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Request messages received. It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

EntityDef.name: ss7messagetermdt1
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Data Form 1 messages received (Connection Oriented data). It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

EntityDef.name: ss7messagetermrlsd
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Released messages received. It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

EntityDef.name: ss7noofcurrrunconntot

The gauge is only applicable for an #SGSN# with #WCDMA# access, but is registered also for an SGSN without WCDMA access if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is greater than zero for any local SAP instance.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_attauthprocsmmeusim
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #EPS# authentication challenges that are started within this #MME# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_attsecmodeprocsmmeusim
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Security Mode Control procedures started within this #MME# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#. The resending of the Security Mode Command message is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_attachauthfailmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Authentication Reject messages sent by the MME during the Attach procedure. The authentication rejection due to timeout (T3460) is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_aucinfoansfail_5001
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Authentication Information Retrieval procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5001. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Authentication Information Answer message with cause code 5001 (User unknown).

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_aucinfoansfail_5420
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed Authentication Information Retrieval procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5420. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Authentication Information Answer message with cause code 5420 (Unknown EPS subscription).

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_authfailue_20_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 20 (MAC failure). The counter is increased whenever the UE detects an incorrect authentication parameter in the Authentication Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_authfailue_21_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 21 (Sync failure). The counter is increased whenever the UE detects an incorrect SQN or a SQN is out of range.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_authfailue_26_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 26 (Non-EPS authentication unacceptable). The counter is increased whenever the UE detects an incorrect authentication parameter in the Authentication Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_identificationatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Identification Request procedures initiated by the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_identificationsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Identification procedures initiated by the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_identityatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Identity Request procedures initiated by the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_identitysucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Identity procedures initiated by the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_succauthprocsmmeusim
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #EPS# authentication challenges that are started within this #MME# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_succsecmodeprocsmmeusim
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Security Mode Control procedures within this #MME# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_tauinterauthfailmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Authentication Reject messages sent by the MME during the Inter-MME TAU procedure. The authentication rejection due to timeout (T3460) is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_tauinteriratauthfailmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication reject messages sent by the MME during the inter-node ISC TAU procedures (with RAT change). The authentication rejection due to (T3460) timeout is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sec_tauintrairatauthfailmme_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication reject messages sent by the MME during the intra-node ISC TAU procedures (with RAT change). The authentication rejection due to (T3460) timeout is not counted.

EntityDef.name: sec_attauthprocssgsnsim_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area for a subscriber using a #SIM#. Valid for subscribers (#GSM# and #UMTS#) located within #GSM# Access System.

EntityDef.name: sec_attauthprocssgsnusim_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#. Valid for #UMTS# subscribers located within #GSM# Access Systems.

EntityDef.name: sec_attcontextrequestfrompsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SGSN Context Request messages or Context Request messages received from a partner (new) SGSN/MME for a subscriber de-registering from this SGSN. It is incremented at receipt of the "#SGSN# Context Request" message or "Context Request" message from the new #SGSN#/MME.

EntityDef.name: sec_attcontextrequesttopsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #SGSN# Context Request messages or Context Request messages sent to a partner (previous) #SGSN#/MME for subscribers registering afresh in this #SGSN#. Resendings are also counted. It is incremented at transmission of the "#SGSN# Context Request" message or "Context Request" message to the previous #SGSN#/MME.

EntityDef.name: sec_attidentityreqimsi_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Identity Request procedures initiated by this #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: sec_recpoauthfailsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of ciphering and Authentication failures within this #SGSN# area.

EntityDef.name: sec_succauthprocssgsnsim_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area, for a subscriber using a #SIM#. Valid for subscribers (#GSM# and #UMTS#) located within #GSM# Access System.

EntityDef.name: sec_succauthprocssgsnusim_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#. Valid for #UMTS# subscribers located within #GSM# Access Systems.

EntityDef.name: sec_succcontextrequesttopsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully replied #SGSN# Context Request messages or Context Request messages that were sent to a partner (previous) #SGSN#/MME. It is incremented at receipt of the "#SGSN# Context Response" message or "Context Response" message from the previous #SGSN#/MME.

EntityDef.name: sec_succidentityreqimsi_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Identity Request procedures initiated by this #SGSN#.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #MAP# requests for authentication sets that were sent to the #HLR#. Note! All #MAP# versions are counted.

EntityDef.name: sec_emptyresponsesforauthsetsfromhlr
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of empty responses to the #MAP# request for authentication sets that were sent to the #HLR#. Note! All #MAP# versions are counted.

EntityDef.name: sec_attsecmode
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of security mode control procedures started by the #SGSN#.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access to WCDMA.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xsucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access to WCDMA.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xunsuccctxtnotfound_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access to LTE. This counter is increased when the PGW rejects the Create Session Request with cause code #64 (Context Not Found).

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xunsuccctxtnotfound_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access to WCDMA. This counter is increased when the PGW rejects the Create Session Request with cause code #64 (Context Not Found).

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xunsuccemcctxtnotfound_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S2x-based (without optimizations) emergency PDN handovers from non-3GPP access to LTE. This counter is incremented when the emergency PGW rejects the Create Session Request with the cause code #64 (Context Not Found).

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xunsuccinvalidemcpgwid_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S2x-based (without optimizations) emergency PDN handovers from non-3GPP access to LTE. This counter is incremented when the emergency PGW identity is missing or invalid in the EPS subscription data.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xunsuccinvalidpgwid_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access to LTE. This counter is increased when the PGW identity is missing or invalid in the EPS subscription data.

EntityDef.name: vs_ho_s2xunsuccinvalidpgwid_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S2x-based (without optimizations) handovers from non-3GPP access to WCDMA. This counter is increased when the PGW identity is missing or invalid in the EPS subscription data.

EntityDef.name: sm_nbractpdpcontextra
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active PDP contexts per RA within an SGSN. The gauge is incremented when a new PDP context is activated and decremented when a PDP context is deactivated. For an RA Update, the old RA indexed gauge is decremented and the new RA indexed gauge is incremented.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_actdedicatedepsbeareratt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Activation procedure attempts between the #MME# and the #UE#. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: sm_actdedicatedepsbearersucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Activation procedures between the #MME# and the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: sm_actdefaultbearerredirectrejectedbyimeitac_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections that is rejected by the APN Redirection criteria. This criteria is specified based on the IMEI-TAC of the UE.

EntityDef.name: sm_actdefaultbearerredirecttosubscribedapn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed APN of the lowest context ID per MME.

EntityDef.name: sm_actdefaultbearerredirecttosubscribeddefaultapn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed default APN per MME.

EntityDef.name: sm_deactepsdedicatedbeareratt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures attempted by the #MME#. The counter is not incremented when resending a Deactivate EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: sm_deactepsdedicatedbearersucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures initiated by the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: sm_modepsbeareratt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #EPS# Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Modify #EPS# Bearer Context Request message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: sm_modepsbearersucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #EPS# Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Modify #EPS# Bearer Context Accept message arrives at the #MME#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actbearernoipv4_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed EPS Bearer Activation procedures with no IPv4 address in the PGW control plane or user plane. #Note: Both default bearer and dedicated bearer procedures are counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdedicatedbeareremcatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Activation procedure attempts between the #MME# and the #UE# for #IMS# emergency service. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdedicatedbeareremcsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Activation procedures between the #MME# and the #UE# for #IMS# emergency service.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdedicatedepsgbrbeareratt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Activation procedure attempts for GBR bearers between the MME and the UE. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Request for GBR bearers to the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdedicatedepsgbrbearersucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Activation procedures for GBR bearers between the MME and the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbearerapnconverted_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN conversions in the default bearer activation procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbeareremcatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted default #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures between #MME# and #UE# for #IMS# emergency service. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbeareremchoatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted default #EPS# Bearer activation procedures between the #MME# and a #UE# for handover of #IMS# emergency service from non-3GPP access networks. The counter is not incremented when the MME resends an Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbeareremchosucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed default #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures towards a #UE# for handover of #IMS# emergency service from non-3GPP access networks.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbeareremcsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed default #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures towards #UE# for #IMS# emergency service.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultepsbeareratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Request messages. The counter is increased whenever this message is sent from the MME to the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultepsbearersucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Accept messages. The counter is increased whenever this message is sent from the UE to the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_attactbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_attdeactbearerue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #EPS# bearers, both default and dedicated, that are disconnected by the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_attdeactdefaultbearerduetopgwresel_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDN reactivations triggered by the MME due to PGW reselection.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbeareratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent on S11 to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers included in the request. Note: The Create Bearer Request message included in the Create Session Response message sent to the MME is also taken into calculation.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbeareremcatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent on S11 to the #MME# for IMS emergency service, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers included in the request. Note: The Create Bearer Request message included in the Create Session Response message sent to the MME is also taken into calculation.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbeareremcsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent on S11 to the #MME# for IMS emergency service, this counter is incremented with the number of successfully activated bearers included in the request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerfail_102
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers that were not activated because the UE was in suspend status, and the MME was unable to page the UE. A response with cause code 102 (Unable to page UE due to Suspension) is returned to the #SGW#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerfail_68
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, because the feature 'Dedicated bearers' is 'Off.' A response with cause code 68 (Service not supported) is returned to the Serving Gateway. (Please note that this counter does not affect any KPI.)

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerfail_87_90
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, due to that the #UE# does not respond or due to that MME is unable to page the UE. A response with cause code 87 (UE not responding) or cause code 90 (Unable to page UE) is returned to the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerfail_88
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, due to that the #UE# rejects the activation attempt. A response with cause code 88 (UE refuses) is returned to the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerfailfwa_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, due to that the number of paging attempts is set to 0. Cause code 90 (Unable to page UE) is returned to the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearersucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each Create Bearer Request message sent on S11 to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of successfully activated bearers included in the request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_createdefaults5s8bearermmeatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages. The counter is increased whenever this message is sent from the MME to the SGW. The Create Session Request message might include one default bearer and multiple dedicated bearers.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_createdefaults5s8bearermmesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with cause code 16 (Request accepted). The counter is increased whenever the MME receives this message from the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_createindirectdataforwardingtunnelatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Indirect Data Forwarding Tunnel Request messages. The counter is incremented when this message is sent from the MME to the SGW excluding the retransmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_createindirectdataforwardingtunnelsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Create Indirect Data Forwarding Tunnel Response messages. The counter is incremented when this message is received by the MME from the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_ddnrecdinsr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Downlink Data Notification messages received by the MME from the SGW in the UE-triggered Service Request procedure. This counter is incremented when the MME receives a Downlink Data Notification message while waiting for the S1-AP Initial Context Setup Response message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_ddnmessage_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Downlink Data Notification messages received by the MME from the SGW. This counter is incremented when the MME receives the Downlink Data Notification message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_ddnamessage_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge messages sent from the MME to the SGW. This counter is incremented when a Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge message is sent from the MME to the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_ddnamessagewiththrottling_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge messages with DL low priority traffic Throttling IE sent from the MME to the SGW. This counter is incremented when a Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge message with DL low priority traffic Throttling IE is sent from the MME to the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpdnhsspcscfinit_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of the Delete Session Request messages sent by the MME to delete the IMS PDN (or detach the UE if the deleted PDN is the last PDN of the UE) when the MME receives the Insert Subscriber Data Request message from the HSS. The Insert Subscriber Data Request message includes the IDR-Flags with the P-CSCF Restoration Request bit set.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_deletededicatedbeareratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures received from the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_deletededicatedbearersucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures sent to the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_deleteindirectdataforwardingtunnelatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Delete Indirect Data Forwarding Tunnel Request messages. The counter is incremented when this message is sent from the MME to the SGW excluding the retransmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_deleteindirectdataforwardingtunnelsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Delete Indirect Data Forwarding Tunnel Response messages. The counter is incremented when this message is received by the MME from the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_emcpdnconnectivityuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of stand-alone PDN Connectivity Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_erabmodconfirm_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of E-RAB Modification Confirm messages sent from the #MME# to the #eNodeB# over the S1 interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_erabmodindication_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of E-RAB Modification Indication messages received in the #MME# from the #eNodeB# over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the message is received at the application level, before the Dual Connectivity Support feature state check.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_esmdatatransportdownlink_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Esm Data Transport messages sent from MME to the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_esmdatatransportuplinkatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Esm Data Transport messages sent from the UE to MME. This counter is also incremented when a Control Plane Service Request message contains an Esm Data Transport message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_esmdatatransportuplinkfail_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Esm Data Transport messages sent from the UE to MME, which MME has discarded. This counter is also incremented when a Control Plane Service Request message contains such an Esm Data Transport message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_extrambrwithprainfoforendc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Presence Reporting Area (PRA) information used for EN-DC reporting through the extra Modify Bearer Request message. The counter is incremented when the MME sends an extra Modify Bearer Request and the message includes the PRA Information with the flag "inside" or "outside".

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_gbrdeacttimercancelled_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer is cancelled.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_gbrdeacttimercancelledduetopaging_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer is cancelled due to paging triggered by downlink payload.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_gbrdeacttimerexpired_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer expires.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_gbrdeacttimerrunninguereturn_e
vs_sm_gbrdeacttimerstarted_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer is started in the MME to delay the deactivation of the GBR bearers when Timer-Based Deactivation of GBR Bearers is enabled.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_mbreqwithdstchangeforsr_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of DST change reporting through the Modify Bearer Request message in the service request procedure. The counter is incremented when the MME sends a Modify Bearer Request in the service request procedure and the message includes the UE Time Zone IE with the DST adjustment change but excludes the User Location Information IE. Note: The DST change reporting caused by the time zone configuration change is not recorded in this counter. For more information about time zone configuration, see LTE Time Zones (CLI).

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modepsbearercmdatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Modify Bearer Command procedures initiated by the MME. Note: The measured data of the counter is incremented when Modify Bearer Command message is sent from the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modepsbearercmdsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful responses of Modify Bearer Command procedures received from SGW. Note: The measured data of the counter is incremented when Update Bearer Request message is received from SGW in response to Modify Bearer Command.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #PDN# Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the #MME#. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerupdatefailfwa_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the PDN Gateway. This counter is incremented when the update bearer procedure is failed due to that the number of paging attempts is set to 0. Cause code 90 (Unable to page UE) is returned to Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of an unsuccessful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerupdatesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #PDN# Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active EPS bearers, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new EPS bearer is activated and decremented when an EPS bearer is deactivated. Note:Both default and dedicated bearers are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractbeareremc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active #EPS# bearers established for #IMS# Emergency Service, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new #EPS# bearer is activated for #IMS# Emergency Service and decremented when an #EPS# bearer for #IMS# Emergency Service is deactivated. #Note:Both default and dedicated bearers for #IMS# Emergency Service are counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractdefaultbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active default #EPS# bearers, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new default #EPS# bearer is activated and decremented when a default #EPS# bearer is deactivated.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractdefaultbeareremc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active default #EPS# bearers for #IMS# emergency service, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new default #EPS# bearer is activated for #IMS# Emergency Service and decremented when a default #EPS# bearer for #IMS# Emergency Service is deactivated.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractprasessions_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDN Connections established with an active Presence Reporting Area (PRA) session. The gauge is incremented when a PRA session is activated for a PDN Connection. The gauge is decremented when a PRA session is deactivated or when a PDN Connection with an active PRA session is removed.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbrecmconnecteddefaultbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active default EPS bearers when the UE is in the ECM_CONNECTED state. The gauge is incremented when a new default EPS bearer is activated or the UE is changed to the ECM_CONNECTED state due to mobility procedures. The gauge is decremented when a default EPS bearer is deactivated or the UE is changed to the ECM_IDLE state due to mobility procedures. #Note: The CPU may increase if the VS.SM.NbrEcmConnectedDefaultBearer.E gauge is updated frequently, which depends on the traffic model.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbruewithprasessions_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UEs with at least one active Presence Reporting Area (PRA) session. The gauge is incremented when the first PDN Connection for a UE activates a PRA session. The gauge is decremented when the last active PRA session for a UE is deactivated or the last PDN Connection with an active PRA session is removed.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_notificationtoue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Notification messages initiated by the MME to the UE. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Notification message to the UE. Resending of the Notification message is also counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nrusagereportsreceived_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Secondary RAT Usage Data Reports received in the MME from the eNodeB over the S1 interface or received in the MME from a Source MME over the S10 interface. The counter is incremented if the NR Usage Data Reporting feature is active.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nrusagereportssentirpgw_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Secondary RAT Usage Data Reports sent from the MME to the SGW over the S11 interface or sent to the Target MME over the S10 interface with Intended Receiver PGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nrusagereportssentirsgw_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Secondary RAT Usage Data Reports sent from the MME to the SGW over the S11 interface or sent to the Target MME over the S10 interface with Intended Receiver SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pdnconnectivityuscdetached_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of PDN Connectivity Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a PDN Connectivity Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pdnconnectivityuscdiscarded_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of stand-alone PDN Connectivity Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pdnconnectivityuscrejected_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of PDN Connectivity Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a PDN Connectivity Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pcscfrestuenotreach_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of HSS based P-CSCF Restoration basic mechanism procedures, during which the MME fails to send the IMS PDN deactivation and reactivation request to the UE when the UE is in the ECM_IDLE state. The counter is incremented when paging or service request fails or is aborted during HSS based P-CSCF Restoration basic mechanism procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pcscfrestorationindgwatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Request messages sent by the MME to the SGW with the P-CSCF Restoration Indication flag set.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pcscfrestorationindgwsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Response messages received by the MME to the Modify Bearer Request messages with the P-CSCF Restoration Indication flag, excluding the Modify Bearer Response messages with cause codes explicitly indicating that the P-CSCF restoration indication has not reached the PGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pdnconnrejectwithbackofftimer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the SGSN-MME included a Back-Off time IE in the PDN Connectivity Reject message because of APN-based congestion. This applies for the standalone PDN Connectivity Request and the Attach procedures.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pdnconnectivityrejectduetoapnrestriction_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of standalone PDN Connectivity Request procedures that have been rejected due to APN restriction in the MME. The counter is incremented when a standalone PDN Connectivity Reject message is sent to the UE because the resolved APN is restricted from EPS services by local configuration in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_praforendcsuppressedidletoconn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Presence Reporting Area (PRA) Information used for EN-DC suppressed and not reported to the PGW when the UE turns to the connected state from the idle state, including timer cancellation because the PRA status is changed to the last reported PRA status again, UE turning to idle, PRA stopped by PGW or PDN disconnected.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_prainforendcsent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Presence Reporting Area (PRA) information with "inside" flag used for EN-DC is sent. The counter is incremented each time the PRA information is included in a message sent to the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_prainforendcsuppressedconn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Presence Reporting Area (PRA) Information with the flag "inside" used for EN-DC suppressed and not reported to the PGW when the UE is in the ECM connected state, including timer cancellation because the PRA status is changed to "outside" again, UE turning to idle, PRA stopped by PGW or PDN disconnected.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_prainformationsent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times Presence Reporting Area (PRA) Information is sent. This counter is incremented each time PRA Information is included in a message sent to SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_praoutforendcsent_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Presence Reporting Area (PRA) information with "outside" flag used for EN-DC is sent. The counter is incremented each time the PRA information is included in a message sent to the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_praoutforendcsuppressedconn_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the Presence Reporting Area (PRA) Information with the flag "outside" used for EN-DC suppressed and not reported to the PGW when the UE is in the ECM connected state, including timer cancellation because the PRA status is changed to "inside" again, UE turning to idle, PRA stopped by PGW or PDN disconnected.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_restorepdnconnatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to a new SGW attempting the GW restoration procedure triggered by the S11 link failure. The counter is not increased if the Create Session Request message is retransmitted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_restorepdnconnsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with accepted cause code received from the SGW in the GW restoration procedure triggered by the S11 link failure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_s1relabnormalrnlwithgbrbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases for UEs with GBR bearers when the S1 release cause is a Radio Network Layer category-related cause code, except the following cause codes: - USER_INACTIVITY - INTER_RAT_REDIRECTION - CS_FALLBACK_TRIGGERED - UE_NOT_AVAILABLE_FOR_PS_SERVICE - REDIRECTION_TOWARDS_1XRTT

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_s1relabnormalwithgbrbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases for UEs with GBR bearers when the S1 release cause is any category cause code, except the following cause codes: - USER_INACTIVITY - INTER_RAT_REDIRECTION - CS_FALLBACK_TRIGGERED - UE_NOT_AVAILABLE_FOR_PS_SERVICE - REDIRECTION_TOWARDS_1XRTT

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_s1relradiolostwithgbrbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to the RADIO_CONNECTION_WITH_UE_LOST cause code for UEs with GBR bearers.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_sgwrelocationlinkdown_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of the MME-initiated SGW Relocations due to the S11 link failure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_staticpgwquerysucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful queries in the local static table in the MME for a PGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_staticsgwquerysucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful queries in the local static table in the MME for an SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_succactbearer_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_succdeactbearerue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #EPS# Bearer Deactivation procedures for both default and dedicated bearers.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_uerestorationupongwrestarted_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UEs for which the MME initiated Gateway Restoration procedures when the SGW or the PGW restarted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_unsuccactbearercc27_28_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures per #MME# because of cause code 27 (Unknown or missing access point name) and cause code 28 (Unknown #PDN# address or #PDN# type). The counter is incremented in the following scenarios: - The #MME# receives a Create Session Response message with cause code 78 (Missing or unknown #APN#) from the #SGW#. - The #MME# interrogates the #DNS# resolver and there is a failure, such as name error or undefined default #APN# of the #MME#. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_unsuccactbearercc32_33_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# bearer activation procedures for each #MME# that occur due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDN# Type is not supported or if the request is denied in the #MME# due to subscriber data restriction. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextra_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #RA# within this SGSN. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented as the SGSN identifies the message as a RIL3 Activate PDP Context Request message.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontextra_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations per #RA# within this SGSN. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.

EntityDef.name: local_timestamp
