EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirectrejectedbyimeitac_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections that is rejected by the APN Redirection criteria. This criteria is specified based on the IMEI-TAC of the MS.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttodefaultapn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the SGSN default APN per SGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttoepssubscribedapn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed APN of the lowest context ID when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttosubscribedapn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the subscribed APN per SGSN.
#Note: If the SGSN default APN included in the subscribed data is used as the negotiated APN, this counter will exclude this scenario. Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttosubscribeddefaultapn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed default APN when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontext_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented at the moment when SGSN identifies the message as a #RIL#3 Activate #PDP# Context Request message.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextdyn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation requests where a dynamic #PDP# address is required to be used.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextsgsnhome_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextuscdiscarded_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of attempted Primary PDP Context Activation messages that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies an Activate PDP Context Request message during a control period. Applies to GSM systems only.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactsecondpdpcontext_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activation procedures.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactsecondpdpcontextntwk_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactsecondpdpcontextntwkacptbyms_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activation requests accepted by an MS.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextggsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted GGSN-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextms_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MS-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SGSN-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when sending "Deactivate PDP Context Request" to the #MS# after an "Error indication" is received from the #GGSN#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsncc38_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SGSN-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures with cause code 38, "Network failure". A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsncc39_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SGSN-initiated PDP contexts deactivation procedures with cause code #39, "Reactivation Required". The cause code is sent to the #MS#. One message can handle more PDP contexts if the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsncc8_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PDP context deactivation procedures triggered by the SGSN due to the ODB.

EntityDef.name: sm_attmodpdpcontextms_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-Initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.

EntityDef.name: sm_attmodpdpcontextsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.

EntityDef.name: sm_attupdpdpcontextggsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. An Update #PDP# Context Request message can be sent from a #GGSN# to an #SGSN# to renegotiate the #QoS# of a #PDP# context.
Only attempts at #QoS# renegotiation are counted.

EntityDef.name: sm_attupdpdpcontextsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. This counter is incremented when the SGSN sends an Update PDP Context Request message to the GGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_deactivatedpdpcontextoldsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of deleted PDP contexts in old SGSN instead of transferring to new SGSN, that is when the T3 tunnel expires.

EntityDef.name: sm_nbractpdpcontext_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active #PDP# contexts, that is, the gauge is incremented whenever a new #PDP# context is activated and decremented whenever a #PDP# context is deactivated.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_nbractivepdppersgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of subscribers having an activated #PDP# context, that is subscribers that can send and receive #GPRS# packet data. The gauge is incremented when a subscriber activates the first context and decremented when the subscriber deactivates the last context.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_notdeactivatedpdpcontextoldsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDP contexts deactivated by the old SGSN after the contexts were transferred to the new SGSN. The reason is that the old SGSN aborted the ISRAU procedure when the MS re-entered the old SGSN's service area prior to the old SGSN receiving a CANCEL LOCATION message from the HLR.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontext_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontextdyn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations where a dynamic #PDP# address is used.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontextsgsnhome_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Number of successful primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactsecondpdpcontext_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactsecondpdpcontextntwk_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_succdeactpdpcontextggsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #GGSN#. For these context deactivations, the #MS# has accepted the #PDP# context deactivation. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_succdeactpdpcontextms_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #PDP# context deactivations. For these context deactivations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully (that is, deletion of the #PDP# context). A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_succdeactpdpcontextsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #SGSN#. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when receiving "Delete PDP Context Response" from the #GGSN# for the cases when no "Deactivate PDP Context Response" can be received from the #MS# since no "Deactivate PDP Context Request" was sent to the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_succmodpdpcontextms_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #MS#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a Modify PDP Context Accept message is sent to the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: sm_succmodpdpcontextsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a positive Modify PDP Context Accept message is received from the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: sm_succupdpdpcontextggsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #GGSN#-Initiated #PDP# context update procedures for #QoS# renegotiation. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #SGSN#.
Only #QoS# renegotiation procedures are counted.

EntityDef.name: sm_succupdpdpcontextsgsn_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #GGSN#.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc26_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 26 (Insufficient resources). The reject can be caused due to, for example, sustained high processor load on one or more #AP#s, or if the hard limit for maximum number of #PDP# contexts is reached.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc27_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #27, "Unknown or missing access point name". It is incremented when the SGSN interrogates the DNS resolver and there is a failure, for example, a name error or the default APN of the SGSN is not defined.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc27_28_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 27 (Unknown or missing access point name), and cause code 28 (Unknown PDP address or PDP type). The counter is incremented when the #SGSN# interrogates the #DNS# resolver and there is a failure - name error or if #APN# (SGSN) is not defined or if requested #PDP# type not sent by #MS# - error.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc29_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 29 (User Authentication Failed). The counter is incremented if the request is rejected by the #GGSN# (#RADIUS#).

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc32_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #32, "Service option not supported". It is incremented if the PDP type is not supported or the #NSAPI# is reserved.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc32_33_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDP# Type is not supported, if #NSAPI# is reserved, or if the request is denied in the #SGSN-MME# due to subscriber data restriction.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc38_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# Context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 38 (Network failure).

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc65_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code 65 (Maximum number of PDP contexts reached). The counter is incremented when the number of simultaneous PDP contexts reaches the limit allowed for an attached user.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc8_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDP context activation procedures rejected by the SGSN due to the ODB.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcamel_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN#, due to #PDP# context activation denial, received from the gsmSCF. The counter is incremented when a #CAMEL# release message is received from the gsmSCF.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbearers4att_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to the #SGW# in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Request message is sent to the #SGW#, excluding the retransmission in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbearers4succ_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with success received from the #SGW# in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Response message is received from the #SGW# in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actpdpcontextapnconverted_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN conversions in the PDP context activation procedure for GSM.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitpdnatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures received from the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitpdnsucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures sent to the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modbearers4att_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Request messages sent to the #SGW# in #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Modify Bearer Request message is sent to the #SGW# excluding the retransmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modbearers4succ_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Response messages with success received from the #SGW# in #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a positive Modify Bearer Response message is received from the #SGW#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearernoqosupdateatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearernoqosupdatesucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerqosupdateatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerqosupdatesucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractbearer_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active S4 mode PDP contexts in the GSM network, that is, the gauge is incremented in the GSM network whenever a new S4 mode PDP context mode is activated and decremented in the GSM network whenever an S4 mode PDP context is deactivated.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbrsubwithactbearer_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of subscribers in the GSM network having an activated S4 mode PDP context, that is, subscribers that can send and receive GPRS packet data. The gauge is incremented in the GSM network when a subscriber activates the first S4 mode PDP context and decremented in the GSM network when the subscriber deactivates the last S4 mode PDP context.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_randowngrades4qos_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDP Contexts of which QoS is downgraded by the RAN during primary PDP Context Activation procedure in the S4-SGSN.

EntityDef.name: gprssmsgsndeactivations
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of #PDP# Context Deactivations per #SGSN# of the PDP Contexts that has been active in SGSN. The counter is also incremented when a PDP Context is moved from one system to another (that is #ISC#) and when a PDP Context is moved from one SGSN to another (that is #ISRAU#). A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: gprssmsgsnunsuccessfulactivations
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME#. The counter is incremented when an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Reject or an SM Status message is sent as a response when an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Request is unsuccessful.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high activation failure rates, typically caused by misconfigured #MS#s using disallowed #APN#s. In this case the resulting cause code is 28 (Unknown #PDP# address or #PDP# type) or 33 (Requested service option not subscribed). If so, check the routines for providing #MS# configuration. #RADIUS# problems are also a common cause of high failure rates. In this case the resulting cause code is 29 (User authentication failed). The alarm can be caused by #GGSN# or #RADIUS# unavailability.

EntityDef.name: gprssmsgsnunsuccessfulmodifications
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
The gprsSmSgsnUnsuccessfulModifications measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# context modifications per #SGSN-MME#.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high modification failure rate, typically caused by radio coverage problems or #GGSN# unavailability.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_homeapnoireplaceatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of DNS query attempts with APN-OI-Replacement, while the UE is a home subscriber. This counter is deprecated now and is replaced by VS.SM.HomeApnOiReplaceAtt in the SGSN-MME_Session_SM group

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_homeapnoireplacesucc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful DNS query procedures with APN-OI-Replacement, while the UE is a home subscriber. This counter is deprecated now and is replaced by VS.SM.HomeApnOiReplaceSucc in the SGSN-MME_Session_SM group

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextra_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #RA# within this SGSN. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented as the SGSN identifies the message as a RIL3 Activate PDP Context Request message.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontextra_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations per #RA# within this SGSN. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirectrejectedbyimeitac_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections that is rejected by the APN Redirection criteria. This criteria is specified based on the IMEI-TAC of the MS.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttodefaultapn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the SGSN default APN per SGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttoepssubscribedapn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed APN of the lowest context ID when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttosubscribedapn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the subscribed APN per SGSN.
#Note: If the SGSN default APN included in the subscribed data is used as the negotiated APN, this counter will exclude this scenario. Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontextredirecttosubscribeddefaultapn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed default APN when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_actpdpcontexts4ignored_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of ignored S4 primary PDP Context Activation procedures. The counter is increased when a new S4 primary PDP context activation request is ignored due to the first primary PDP context being activated or being deactivated.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontext_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented at the moment when #SGSN# identifies the message as a #RIL#3 Activate #PDP# Context Request message.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextdyn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation requests where a dynamic #PDP# address is required to be used.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextsgsnhome_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactpdpcontextuscdiscarded_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of attempted Primary PDP Context Activation messages that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control activated, and when it identifies a Activate PDP Context Request message during a control period. Applies to WCDMA systems only.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactsecondpdpcontext_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactsecondpdpcontextntwk_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_attactsecondpdpcontextntwkacptbyms_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activation requests accepted by MS.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextggsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted GGSN-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextms_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MS-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SGSN-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when sending "Deactivate PDP Context Request" to the #MS# after an "Error indication" is received from the #GGSN#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsncc38_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SGSN-initiated PDP context deactivation procedures with cause code 38 "Network failure". A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsncc39_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SGSN-initiated PDP contexts deactivation procedures cause code 39 "Reactivation Required". The cause code is sent to the #MS#. One message can handle more PDP contexts if the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_attdeactpdpcontextsgsncc8_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PDP context deactivation procedures triggered by the SGSN due to the ODB.

EntityDef.name: sm_attmodpdpcontextms_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.

EntityDef.name: sm_attmodpdpcontextsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.

EntityDef.name: sm_attrabassignment
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #RAB# setup attempts. The counter is incremented according to the number of required RABs setup included in RAB assignment request that is sent to the #RNC# with #IE# 'Setup RAB'.

EntityDef.name: sm_attrabmodps
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted RAB Modify Request procedures. It is incremented when RAB Modify Request is received.

EntityDef.name: sm_attupdpdpcontextggsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. An Update #PDP# Context Request message can be sent from a #GGSN# to an #SGSN# to renegotiate the #QoS# of a #PDP# context.
Only attempts at #QoS# negotiation are counted.

EntityDef.name: sm_attupdpdpcontextsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. This counter is incremented when the SGSN sends an Update PDP Context Request message to the GGSN.

EntityDef.name: sm_deactivatedpdpcontextoldsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of deleted PDP contexts in old SGSN instead of transferring to new SGSN, that is when the T3 tunnel expires.

EntityDef.name: sm_nbractpdpcontext_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active #PDP# contexts, that is, the gauge is incremented whenever a new #PDP# context is activated and decremented whenever a #PDP# context is deactivated.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication that the #SGSN-MME# is approaching the maximum number of activated #PDP# contexts. Offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #RNC#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#.

EntityDef.name: sm_nbractivepdpsapprfor3gdt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active #PDP# contexts approved for 3G Direct Tunnel, that is, a 3G Direct Tunnel is set up for these PDP contexts when they run payload. Note: This gauge is not supervised, no threshold and clearing level apply.

EntityDef.name: sm_nbractivepdppersgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of mobile subscribers with activated #PDP# contexts, that is, subscribers that can send and receive #GPRS# packet data.The gauge is incremented when a subscriber activates the first context and decremented when the subscriber deactivates the last context.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: sm_notdeactivatedpdpcontextoldsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDP contexts deactivated by the old SGSN after the contexts were transferred to the new SGSN. The reason is that the old SGSN aborted the ISRAU procedure when the MS re-entered the old SGSN's service area prior to the old SGSN receiving a CANCEL LOCATION message from the HLR.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontext_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontextdyn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations where a dynamic #PDP# address is used.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactpdpcontextsgsnhome_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: Number of successful primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactsecondpdpcontext_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_succactsecondpdpcontextntwk_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

EntityDef.name: sm_succdeactpdpcontextggsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #GGSN#. For these context deactivations, the #MS# has accepted the #PDP# context deactivation. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_succdeactpdpcontextms_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #PDP# context deactivations. For these context deactivations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully (that is, deletion of the #PDP# context). A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_succdeactpdpcontextsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #SGSN#. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when receiving "Delete PDP Context Response" from the #GGSN# for the cases when no "Deactivate PDP Context Response" can be received from the #MS# since no "Deactivate PDP Context Request" was sent to the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

EntityDef.name: sm_succmodpdpcontextms_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #MS#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a Modify PDP Context Accept message is sent to the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: sm_succmodpdpcontextsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a positive Modify PDP Context Accept message is received from the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: sm_succrabassignment
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #RAB# setups. It is incremented when a RAB Assignment Response message is received, indicating successful #RAB# setup.

EntityDef.name: sm_succupdpdpcontextggsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #GGSN#-Initiated #PDP# context update procedures for #QoS# renegotiation. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #SGSN#.
Only #QoS# renegotiation procedures are counted.

EntityDef.name: sm_succupdpdpcontextsgsn_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #GGSN#.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontext_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME#. The counter is incremented when an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Reject or an SM Status message is sent as a response if an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Request is unsuccessful.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high activation failure rates, typically caused by misconfigured #MS#s using disallowed #APN#s. In this case the resulting cause code is 28 (Unknown #PDP# address or #PDP# type) or 33 (Requested service option not subscribed). If so, check the routines for providing #MS# configuration. #RADIUS# problems are also a common cause of high failure rates. In this case the resulting cause code is 29 (User authentication failed). The alarm can be caused by #GGSN# or #RADIUS# unavailability.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc26_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 26 (Insufficient resources). The reject can be caused due to, for example, sustained high processor load on one or more #AP#s, or if hard limit is applied for PDP context capacity and the number of PDP context reaches the licensed capacity limit of the #SGSN-MME#.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc27_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #27, "Unknown or missing access point name". It is incremented when the SGSN interrogates the DNS resolver and there is a failure, for example, a name error or the default APN of the SGSN is not defined.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc27_28_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 27 (Unknown or missing access point name), and cause code 28 (Unknown PDP address or PDP type). The counter is incremented when the #SGSN# interrogates the #DNS# resolver and there is a failure - name error or if #APN# (SGSN) is not defined or if requested #PDP# type not sent by #MS# - error.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc29_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 29 (User Authentication Failed). The counter is incremented if the request is rejected by the #GGSN# (#RADIUS#).

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc32_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #32, "Service option not supported". It is incremented if the PDP type is not supported or the #NSAPI# is reserved.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc32_33_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# Context activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDP# Type is not supported, if #NSAPI# is reserved or if the request is denied in the #SGSN-MME# due to subscriber data restriction.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc38_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 38 (Network failure).

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc65_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code 65 (Maximum number of PDP contexts reached). The counter is incremented when the number of simultaneous PDP contexts reaches the limit allowed for an attached user.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcc8_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDP context activation procedures rejected by the SGSN due to the ODB.

EntityDef.name: sm_unsuccactpdpcontextcamel_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN#, due to PDP context activation denial, received from the gsmSCF. The counter is incremented when a CAMEL release message is received from the gsmSCF.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbearers4att_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to the SGW in WCDMA, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Request message is sent to the SGW excluding the retransmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actdefaultbearers4succ_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages received from the SGW with success in WCDMA, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Response message is received from the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actpgwinitdedicatedbeareratt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# Context Activation Procedure using S4, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers included in the Create Bearer Request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actpgwinitdedicatedbearersucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: For each attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# Context Activation Procedure using S4, this counter is incremented with the number of successfully activated bearers included in the Create Bearer Response.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actpdpcontextapnconverted_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of APN conversions in the PDP context activation procedure for UMTS.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actpdpcontextuscdetached_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Activate PDP Context Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Activate PDP Context Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actpdpcontextuscrejected_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Activate PDP Context Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Activate PDP Context Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_bearerqosmismatch_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of EPS bearers with QoS mismatch between the S4-SGSN and PGW. It is incremented if the S4-SGSN does not receive a PGW-initiated QoS modification within a certain time after an EPS bearer has been downgraded due to QoS policy map during RAU from the S4-SGSN/MME to the S4-SGSN or handover from the MME to the S4-SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_deactmsinitdedicatedbeareratt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-Initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedures over the S4 interface. The value is increased whenever the S4-#SGSN# receives a Deactivate PDP Context Request message from the MS.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_deactmsinitdedicatedbearersucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #MS#-Initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedures over the S4 interface. The value is increased when the #S4-SGSN# sends a Deactivate PDP Context Accept message to the #MS#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitdedicatedbeareratt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of bearers included in the Delete Bearer Request. The value is increased whenever a Delete Bearer Request is sent during each attempted #MS#-, #SGSN#-, or #PGW#-initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedure over the S4 interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitdedicatedbearersucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully deactivated bearers during each #MS#-, #SGSN#-, or #PGW#-initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedure over the S4 interface. The value is increased whenever a bearer is deactivated in the Delete Bearer Response message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitpdnatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures received from the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitpdnsucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures sent to the Serving Gateway.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delsgsninitdedicatedbeareratt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of bearers included in the Delete Bearer Command. The value is increased whenever a Delete Bearer Command is sent during each attempted #MS#- or #SGSN#-initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedure over the S4 interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modbearercmds4att_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Command messages sent to the SGW for WCDMA access. The measured data of this counter is incremented when a Modify Bearer Command message is sent to the SGW, excluding the retransmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modbearercmds4succ_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Modify Bearer Command responses (Update Bearer Request messages) received from the SGW for WCDMA access. The measured data of this counter is incremented when an Update Bearer Request message is received from the SGW.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modbearers4att_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Request messages sent to the #SGW# in #WCDMA#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Modify Bearer Request message is sent to the #SGW# excluding the retransmission.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modbearers4succ_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Response messages with success received from the #SGW# in #WCDMA#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a positive Modify Bearer Response message is received from the #SGW#.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearernoqosupdateatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearernoqosupdatesucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerqosupdateatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_modpgwinitbearerqosupdatesucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractbearer_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active S4 mode PDP contexts in WCDMA network, that is, the gauge is incremented in WCDMA whenever a new PDP context of S4 mode is activated and decremented in WCDMA whenever a PDP context of S4 mode is deactivated.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractbearerfor3gdt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active bearers approved for 3G Direct Tunnel on the SGSN supporting the S4 interface with #UMTS# access, that is, a 3G Direct Tunnel is set up for these bearers.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractdefaultbearer_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of active default EPS bearers in S4-SGSN, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new default EPS bearer is activated and decremented when a default EPS bearer is deactivated in S4-SGSN.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbrsubwithactbearer_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of subscribers in WCDMA network having an activated PDP context of S4 mode, that is subscribers that can send and receive GPRS packet data. The gauge is incremented in WCDMA network when a subscriber activates the first context of S4 mode and decremented in WCDMA network when the subscriber deactivates the last context of S4 mode.
#Note: After a change to the #PDP# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #PDP# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbrswitchfrom3gdtforpdp_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of times the tunnel mode is switched from being of one tunnel (or direct tunnel) to two-tunnel.
Note: This measurement is only applicable for the tunnel switch due to Service Request Frequency.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbrswitchto3gdtforpdp_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of times the tunnel mode is switched from being of two-tunnels to one tunnel (or direct tunnel).
Note: This measurement is only applicable for the tunnel switch due to Service Request Frequency.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_randowngrades4qos_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of PDP Contexts of which QoS is downgraded by the RAN during primary PDP Context Activation procedure in the S4-SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_reactpdnconnonsgwatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to the restarted SGW in the Gateway Restoration procedure for WCDMA S4-SGSN. The counter does not increase if the Create Session Request message is retransmitted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_reactpdnconnonsgwsucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with "Accept" types of cause values received from the SGW in the Gateway Restoration procedure for WCDMA S4-SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_curlocrequesthssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Current Location requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating Current Location Request is received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_emcpgwidchangehssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of HSS-initiated PGW ID updates. The Emergency PGW ID information is contained in an Insert Subscriber Data Request message. This counter is incremented when one of the following conditions is met: - When the feature bit Emergency Service Continuity is updated from unsupported to supported with a valid Emergency PGW ID information. - When the feature bit Emergency Service Continuity is updated from supported to unsupported and the previous Emergency PGW ID information is valid. - When the feature bit Emergency Service Continuity is set and it will not change after the Insert Subscriber Data Request, and the Emergency PGW ID information is updated from an empty value to a valid value, or vice versa. - When the feature bit Emergency Service Continuity is set and it will not change after the Insert Subscriber Data Request, and the Emergency PGW ID information is updated from a valid value to another valid value.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locrequesthssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted EPS Location Information requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating EPS Location Information Request is received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_notifyhssemcpgwidchange
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the notification procedure is used to inform the HSS about the assignment or the change of a dynamically allocated PGW for a non-roaming authenticated UE. This counter is incremented when a Notify Request message including the updated emergency PGW ID information is sent to the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_notifyhsspgwidchange
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times the notification procedure is used to inform the HSS about the assignment or change of a dynamically allocated PGW for an APN. This counter increases when a Notify Request message, including updated PGW ID information is sent to the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pcscfrestorehssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of the Insert Subscriber Data Request messages from the HSS requiring for P-CSCF Restoration, which is indicated by Bit8 in IDR-Flag.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_pgwidchangehssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of HSS-initiated PGW ID updates. This counter increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message, including updated PGW ID information is received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_timerbasedpurgedue
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of detached UEs that are purged when the timer-based purge function is enabled and the UE purge timer expires.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_tzrequesthssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Local Time Zone requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating Local Time Zone Request is received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_urrprequesthssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted UE Reachability requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating UE Reachability Request is received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_usrequesthssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted EPS User State requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating EPS User State Request is received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitpdncc4att_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation. This counter is increased when the SGW receives the Delete Bearer Request message with cause code #4 (RAT changed from 3GPP to Non-3GPP).

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_delpgwinitpdncc4succ_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation. This counter is increased when the SGW receives the Delete Bearer Request message with cause code #4 (RAT changed from 3GPP to Non-3GPP) and the PDN Deactivation procedure is successful.

EntityDef.name: sub_deletesubscrdatahssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted delete subscriber data requests received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: sub_insertsubscrdatahssatt
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted insert subscriber data requests received from the HSS.

EntityDef.name: vs_sub_hssresetwithfullimsi
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of messages regarding HSS Reset with full IMSI. This measurement is incremented when a Reset Request message including one or more full IMSIs (15 digits) is received from the HSS.
Note: For the message including both full IMSI and IMSI prefix, the message is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_nbractsessions_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active Smp sessions in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_nbruewithsession_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UEs holding at least one active Smp session in the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sapcpgwquery_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number that the MME queries the PGW address that is returned by the SAPC for PDN connections. The counter is incremented each time the MME attempts to query the PGW address and the PGW address from SAPC is available. For example, the MME selects the PGW from SAPC to establish PDN connections during Attach or PDN connectivity request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessioninitialatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session establishment in the MME. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the INITIAL_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessioninitialsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session establishments in the MME. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a successful Credit-Control-Answer message with the INITIAL_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionreauthatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session re-authorization from the SAPC. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a Re-Auth-Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionreauthsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session re-authorizations from the SAPC. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a successful Re-Auth-Answer message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionterminate_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Smp session terminations initiated by the MME. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the TERMINATION_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session update by the MME. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the UPDATE_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionupdatesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session updates by the MME. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a successful Credit-Control-Answer message with the UPDATE_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignoredoutboundrequestssapc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of outgoing request messages toward the SAPC that have been rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism. This counter is incremented each time a Credit-Control-Request message toward the SAPC is rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism. Note: This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsnapcpuusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per group of cores running AP functionality on a #PIU# or #VM#. The value is the average #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high #CPU# load. One remedy can be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in a recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case, no action is required.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsnapsuusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the current SU (Scheduler Utilization) usage per group of cores running AP functionality on a #PIU# or #VM#. The value is the average #SU# load measured on a per minute basis.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #SU# load for a longer period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high #SU# load. One remedy can be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in a recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case, no action is required.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsncpuusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per #PIU# or #VM#. The value is the average #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis.
This measurement is not applicable for #CMXB# #PIUs#.
This measurement does not indicate the #CPU# usage for traffic handling on #vLCs#. For #vLC# traffic handling #CPU# usage, use the measurement SYS.gnsLcCpuUsage. Half of the #vLC# #vCPUs# execute Data Plane Development Kit (DPDK) poll mode driver threads that are busy-looping, which leads to 100% #CPU# load. The other half of the #vLC# #vCPUs# execute functions that are not traffic-related and have approximately 0% #CPU# load in normal operation. Therefore, #vLC# #VMs# have a base #CPU# load of 50%. The base #CPU# load for #GPB# #VMs# with integrated #vLCs# equals ((number of #vLC# #CPUs#/2) / total number of #vCPUs#).
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high #CPU# load. One remedy can be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in a recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case, no action is required.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsnlccpuusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the estimated #CPU# usage of the highest utilized core running #LC# functionality on a #VM#. The value is the average #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis.
The value is an estimate of the #CPU# usage for traffic handling on the #vLC#, because the #vLC# executes Data Plane Development Kit (DPDK) poll mode driver threads that are busy-looping at 100% #CPU# load. Therefore, the value cannot be compared with the #CPU# load measured on guest #OS# or cloud infrastructure level. For a #GPB# with integrated #vLC#, the value may show a high base load even without traffic.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high #CPU# load. One remedy can be to scale out with another vLC #VM#.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsnmemusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the current memory usage per processor. This measurement is applicable for all boards except #CMXB#s. The value is the average memory consumption measured on a per minute basis.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high memory usage for a long period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high memory usage.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsnpayloaddpcpuusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per group of cores running Payload DP functionality on a #PIU# or #VM#. The value is the momentary #CPU# load measurement run through a low pass filter. Updated once per minute.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high #CPU# load. One remedy can be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in a recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case, no action is required.

EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of EAB WIFI Access Decision Request messages sent from the MME to the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface. This counter is incremented each time an EAB WIFI Access Decision Request message is sent by the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_accessdecisionsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful EAB WIFI Access Decision Response messages received from the eNodeB. This counter is incremented each time a successful EAB WIFI Access Decision Response message is received from the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_accessresp_e

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_estimatercvd_e

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_estimateresp_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Estimate Response messages sent from the MME to the Wi-Fi Controller. This counter is incremented each time a successful Estimate Response message is sent by the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_firstupdateindicationrcvd_e

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_throughputestimateatt_e

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_throughputestimatesucc_e

EntityDef.name: vs_wifi_uelocationupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UE Location Update messages sent to the Wi-Fi UE Locator over the U1a interface. This counter is incremented each time a UE Location Update message is sent to the Wi-Fi UE Locator.

EntityDef.name: vs_gtp_gtpmessagereceived
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of GTP-C messages received per GTP interface. This measurement type is indexed per GTP-C interface, that is, Gn, S3, S4, S10, S11, S16, Sm, and Sv. The measurement type with index Gn includes messages received over the Gn and Gp interfaces (GTPv0 and GTPv1). Note: For the measurement to measure the number of messages received per GTP-C interface (IP service), each IP service needs to be configured with a different IP service address.

EntityDef.name: vs_gtp_gtpmessagesent

This measurement type is indexed per GTP-C interface, that is, Gn, S3, S4, S10, S11, S16, Sm, and Sv. The measurement type with index Gn includes messages sent over the Gn and Gp interfaces (GTPv0 and GTPv1). Note: For the measurement to measure the number of messages sent per GTP-C interface (IP service), each IP service needs to be configured with a different IP service address.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_nbractsessions_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active Smp sessions in the SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_nbruewithsession_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UEs holding at least one active Smp session in the SGSN.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sapcgwquery_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number that the SGSN queries the GGSN/PGW address that is returned by the SAPC for PDP connections. The counter is incremented each time the SGSN attempts to query the GGSN/PGW address and the GGSN/PGW address from SAPC is available. For example, the SGSN selects the GGSN/PGW from SAPC to establish PDP connections during a primary PDP context activation procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessioninitialatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session establishment in the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the INITIAL_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessioninitialsucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session establishments in the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN receives a successful Credit-Control-Answer message with the INITIAL_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionreauthatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session re-authorization from the SAPC to the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN receives a Re-Auth-Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionreauthsucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session re-authorization from the SAPC to the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a successful Re-Auth-Answer message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionterminate_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Smp session termination procedures initiated by the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the TERMINATION_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionupdateatt_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Smp session update procedures initiated by the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the UPDATE_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionupdatesucc_u
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session update procedures initiated by the SGSN. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN receives a successful Credit-Control-Answer message with the UPDATE_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignoredoutboundrequestssapc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of outgoing request messages toward the SAPC that have been rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism. This counter is incremented each time a Credit-Control-Request message toward the SAPC is rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism. Note: This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actbearerqciatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Default Bearer Activation procedures. This measurement is indexed by QCI. The indexed counter is incremented when the MME receives a PDN Connectivity Request message from the UE and determines the QCI. Note: In the case that the requested QCI can be changed by the network in the Default Bearer Activation procedure, VS.SM.ActBearerQCIAtt.E and VS.SM.ActBearerQCISucc.E cannot be used to calculate the Default Bearer Activation failure ratio per QCI.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_actbearerqcisucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Default Bearer Activation procedures. This measurement is indexed by QCI. The indexed counter is incremented when the MME receives a successful Modify Bearer Response message. Note: In the case that the requested QCI can be changed by the network in the Default Bearer Activation procedure, VS.SM.ActBearerQCIAtt.E and VS.SM.ActBearerQCISucc.E cannot be used to calculate the Default Bearer Activation failure ratio per QCI.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerqciatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted EPS Bearer Activations for dedicated bearers with the indexed QCI on S11, initiated from SGW/PGW towards MME. For each Create Bearer Request for the indexed QCI(s), this counter is incremented with the number of bearers included in the request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_creatededicatedbearerqcisucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful EPS Bearer Activations for dedicated bearers with the indexed QCI on S11, initiated from SGW/PGW towards MME. For each successful Create Bearer Request for the indexed QCI(s), this counter is incremented with the number of successful bearers included in the request.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_enbormmeinitdeletebearerqciatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Deactivation procedures initiated by the eNodeB, or the MME indexed per QCI. The counter is incremented when the MME sends a Delete Bearer Command message over S11 to the SGW, or when the MME sends a Delete Session Request over S11 to SGW. Both default and dedicated bearers are counted, as well as the dedicated bearers that are implicitly deleted when a default bearer is deleted. The measurement will exclude the scenarios where UE triggers the procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_enbormmeinitdeletebearerqcisucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Deactivation procedures initiated by the eNodeB, or the MME indexed per QCI. The counter is incremented when the MME sends a Delete Bearer Response over S11 to SGW, having already sent a Delete Bearer Command to SGW, or when the MME receives a Delete Session Response over S11 from SGW. Both default and dedicated bearers are counted, as well as the dedicated bearers that are implicitly deleted when a default bearer is deleted. MME will internally remove the successful and unsuccessful bearers after the MME sends a Delete Bearer Command or a Delete Session Request. The measurement will exclude the scenarios where UE triggers the procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_nbractbearerqci_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This gauge provides the number of activated EPS bearers (both default and dedicated) per QCI. The gauge is incremented for the used QCI when a new EPS bearer is activated. The gauge is decremented for the used QCI when a new EPS bearer is deactivated. When the QCI is modified for an existing EPS bearer, the gauge is incremented for the new QCI, and decremented for the old QCI.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pgwinitdeletebearerqciatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Deactivation procedures for bearers with the indexed QCIs initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is increased when the MME receives a Delete Bearer Request from SGW without having sent a Delete Bearer Command to SGW. Both Default and Dedicated bearers are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pgwinitdeletebearerqcisucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Deactivation procedures for bearers with the indexed QCIs sent over S11 to the SGW. The counter is increased when the MME sends a successful Delete Bearer Response to SGW without having sent a Delete Bearer Command to SGW. Both Default and Dedicated bearers are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pgwinitmodbearerqciatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the PDN Gateway for bearers indexed per QCI. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message, related to one or multiple bearers, arrives at the MME. This counter is incremented for the new QCI value. Both default and dedicated bearers are counted. The counter is only incremented for Bearer IDs known to the MME.

EntityDef.name: vs_sm_pgwinitmodbearerqcisucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the PDN Gateway for bearers indexed per QCI. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response, related to one or multiple bearers, is sent over S11 to the SGW. This counter is incremented for the new QCI value. Both default and dedicated bearers are counted. The counter is only incremented for Bearer IDs known to the MME.
