EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_nbrattachedcemodeue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs in the Coverage Enhancement (CE) mode. The gauge is incremented when an attached UE enters the CE mode, independently of if Coverage Extension Support, LTE license is granted, or if granted, independently of if the feature is enabled. The gauge is decremented when a UE is out of the CE mode, detaches from, or moves out of the MME.
The UE in the CE mode is identified with the CE mode indication in UE Radio Capability IE included in the UE CAPABILITY INFO INDICATION message from the eNodeB. The gauge is incremented when the MME receives UE CAPABILITY INFO INDICATION message from the eNodeB and the CE mode is indicated in the UE Radio Capability IE.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_nbrattachededrxue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs using eDRX mode. The gauge is incremented when a UE attaches to or moves into MME with eDRX mode activated. The gauge is decremented when a UE detaches from or moves out of MME or deactivates eDRX mode.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_nbrattachedlowcomplexityue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached low-complexity UEs. The counter is incremented when a low-complexity UE attaches to or moves into the MME. The counter is decremented when a low-complexity UE detaches from or moves out of the MME.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_nbrpendingpagingedrxue_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of UEs using eDRX mode with a paging procedure pending. This measurement is incremented when a paging procedure, from the MME to a UE using eDRX mode, is pending. This measurement is decremented when the paging procedure is started or discarded.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingcemodeueatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted Paging procedures initiated for UEs in the Coverage Enhancement (CE) mode. The counter is incremented when a Paging message is sent to the eNodeB at the first transmission. Retransmissions of the same Paging message are not counted. Note: Paging procedures triggered by NTSR or CSSR are not counted in this counter. Paging procedures triggered by NTSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForNTSR.E. Paging procedures triggered by CSSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForCSSR.E.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingcemodeuesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful Paging procedures initiated for UEs in the Coverage Enhancement (CE) mode, irrespective of the paging being an initial Paging message or the resending of the Paging message. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from the UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxueatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted paging procedures from the MME to UEs using eDRX mode. The counter is incremented when a paging message is sent to the eNodeB at the first transmission. Retransmissions of paging messages are not counted. Note: Paging procedures triggered by NTSR or CSSR are not counted in this counter. Paging procedures triggered by NTSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForNTSR.E. Paging procedures triggered by CSSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForCSSR.E.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxuedelayed_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of eDRX paging procedures delayed because the UE is using eDRX mode.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxueptwclosed_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of eDRX paging procedures discarded because the paging time window (PTW) closed at paging timeout.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxuesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures from the MME to UEs using eDRX mode. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or a NAS message from the UE is received while the paging procedure is still active.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_paginglowcomplexityueatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted Paging procedures initiated for low-complexity UEs. The counter is incremented when a Paging message is sent to the eNodeB at the first transmission. Retransmissions of the same Paging message are not counted. Note: Paging procedures triggered by NTSR or CSSR are not counted in this counter. Paging procedures triggered by NTSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForNTSR.E. Paging procedures triggered by CSSR are counted in VS.GeoRed.AttPagingForCSSR.E.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_paginglowcomplexityuesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful Paging procedures initiated for low-complexity UEs, irrespective of the paging being an initial Paging message or the resending of the Paging message. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from the UE is received.

EntityDef.name: sys_gsnss7sctpdpcpuusage
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per group of cores running SS7/SCTP DP functionality on a #PIU# or #VM#. The value is the momentary #CPU# load measurement run through a low pass filter. Updated once per minute.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer period of time, troubleshoot to find the reason for the high #CPU# load. One remedy can be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in a recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case, no action is required.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_downlinkunitdataatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Downlink Unitdata procedures on the SGs-Lite interface. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an SGSLite-DOWNLINK-UNITDATA message from an SDS GW. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_downlinkunitdatasucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Downlink Unitdata procedures on the SGs-Lite interface. This counter is incremented when the MME sends an S1-AP Downlink NAS Transport message to an SDS UE. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_imsidetachatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted IMSI Detach Indication procedures on the SGs-Lite interface. This counter is incremented when the MME sends an SGSLite-IMSI-DETACH-INDICATION message to an SDS GW, excluding the retransmission. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_imsidetachsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Detach Indication procedures on the SGs-Lite interface, initiated within the MME. This counter is incremented when the MME successfully receives an SGSLite-IMSI-DETACH-ACK message from an SDS GW for a UE and the UE context is still present in the MME. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_locationupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Location Update procedures on the SGs-Lite interface, initiated within the MME. This counter is incremented when the MME sends an SGSLite-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message to an SDS GW, excluding the retransmission. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_locationupdatesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Location Update procedures on the SGs-Lite interface, initiated within the MME. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an SGSLite-LOCATION-UPDATE-ACK message with cause code "success" from an SDS GW. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_uplinkunitdataatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Uplink Unitdata procedures on the SGs-Lite interface, initiated within the MME. This counter is incremented when the MME sends an SGSLite-UPLINK-UNITDATA message to an SDS GW, excluding the retransmission. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_sds_uplinkunitdatasucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Uplink Unitdata procedures on the SGs-Lite interface, initiated within the MME. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an SGSLite-UPLINK-ACK message from an SDS GW. Note: This counter is restricted and not for general use.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_connectionlesslppaatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted LPPa Connectionless Information signaling initiated by an E-SMLC within this MME area. Trigger: Receiving a Connectionless Information message with an LPPa container from the E-SMLC over the SLs interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted initial location service request procedures in the #SGSN-MME#, which includes all the LCS Client Types sent to the #E-SMLC# over the SLs interface. Procedures related to resending Location Request messages to alternative E-SMLCs are excluded. Trigger: Sending the initial LCS-AP Location Request message to the #E-SMLC# over the SLs interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestattretry_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of retried Location Request messages in location service request procedures in the SGSN-MME, which includes all the LCS Client Types sent to the E-SMLC over the SLs interface. Trigger: Re-Sending the LCS-AP Location Request message to the next alternative E-SMLC when the response to the previous request fails over the SLs interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful initial location service request procedures in the #SGSN-MME#, which includes all the LCS Client Types sent to the E-SMLC over the SLs interface. Procedures related to resending Location Request messages to alternative E-SMLCs are excluded. Trigger: Reception of the LCS-AP Location Response message from the first selected #E-SMLC# over the SLs interface with a successful result code.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestsuccretry_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful location service request procedures in the SGSN-MME if more than one E-SMLC has been tried. The procedures include all the LCS Client Types sent to the E-SMLC over the SLs interface. Trigger: Reception of the LCS-AP Location Response message from the alternative E-SMLC over the SLs interface with a successful result code.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mtlratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MT-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#, which includes all the LCS Client Types requested from the GMLC over the SLg interface. Trigger: Reception of a Provide Subscriber Location Request message from the #GMLC# over the SLg interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mtlrfailduetopreemption_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of failed MT-LR procedures because of the preemption in the SGSN-MME. The counter is incremented when one MT-LR procedure with non-emergency LCS Client Type is aborted by another MT-LR procedure with emergency LCS Client Type.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mtlrsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful initial #MT-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#, which includes all the LCS Client Types requested from the GMLC over the SLg Interface. The procedure is considered successful when the #E-SMLC# has provided an estimation of the UE's location. Procedures related to resending Location Request messages to alternative E-SMLCs are excluded. Trigger: Sending the Provide Subscriber Location Response message to the #GMLC# over the SLg interface with a successful result code, if only one E-SMLC has been tried during the procedure. Note: The number of successful MT-LR procedures for queued emergency SLg sessions are also counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mtlrsuccretry_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful MT-LR procedures in the SGSN-MME, which includes all the LCS Client Types requested from the GMLC over the SLg interface. The procedure is considered successful when the E-SMLC has provided an estimation of the UE's location. Trigger: Sending the Provide Subscriber Location Response message to the GMLC over the SLg interface with a successful result code, if more than one E-SMLC has been tried during the procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nilratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted SLg #NI-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Sending the Subscriber Location Report message to the #GMLC# over the SLg interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_nilrsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #NI-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Reception of the Subscriber Location Report Ack message from the #GMLC# with a successful result code.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_queueemcmtlrsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #MT-LR# procedures for queued emergency SLg sessions. The queued emergency SLg sessions are considered successful when the #E-SMLC# has provided an estimation of the UE's location for the ongoing emergency positioning request. The counter is incremented when the #MME# sends the Provide Subscriber Location Response message to the #GMLC# over the SLg interface using the existing successful positioning result from the ongoing #MT-LR# procedure.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsforwtableentries
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv4 routes currently in the forwarding table.
The SGSN-MME has the following limits on route numbers: - The SMXB supports a maximum of 40,000 IPv4 routes in the forwarding table of each LC. - The SMXB has no limit on the number of IPv4 routes in the forwarding table of each IP network. - Virtual SGSN-MME supports a maximum of 256 static IPv4 routes per vLC and VPN. - Virtual SGSN-MME supports a maximum of 1,024 static IPv4 routes per vLC. Exceeding these limits causes loss of connectivity.
Do the following when the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: - Reduce the number of static routes configured on the SGSN-MME. - Reduce the number of routes exported to the SGSN-MME from external routers. - If OSPF is used, consider using OSPF NSSA to reduce the number of routes.
Note: When this measurement is used on virtual SGSN-MME, the default alarm-triggering level is 250 and the default alarm-clearing level is 240.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsfragcreates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv4 fragments generated as a result of fragmentation in the indexed logical network on the PIU or VM.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and the control packets of IP routing protocols.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsfragfails
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv4 datagrams discarded because they could not be fragmented in the indexed logical network on the PIU or VM. The cause, for example, can be that the Don't Fragment flag was set in the IP header.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and the control packets of IP routing protocols.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsfragoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv4 datagrams successfully fragmented in the indexed logical network on the PIU or VM.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and the control packets of IP routing protocols.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsoutnoroutes
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv4 datagrams discarded on the indexed logical network as no route is found to transmit them.
This measurement counts payload, signalling, and the control packets of IP routing protocols.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsreasmfails
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of failures detected by the IP reassembly algorithm for each logical network on the PIU or VM. Failures can be, for example, reassembly time-out errors.
The counter value is calculated as follows: (number of IPv4 packet fragments received) - (number of fragments in successfully reassembled IPv4 packets). The counter is updated when an IPv4 packet is successfully reassembled, if the newly calculated value is higher than the current counter value. During the time between two successfully reassembled IPv4 packets, the counter can show an inaccurate value.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsreasmoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of IPv4 datagrams successfully reassembled in the indexed logical network on the PIU or VM.

EntityDef.name: ipstatsreasmreqds
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of IPv4 fragments received and that need to be reassembled in the indexed logical network on the PIU or VM.

This measurement includes the failures counted by all ipv6StatsReasmFails instances.

EntityDef.name: ipv6systemstatsreasmoks
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv6 datagrams successfully reassembled in the SGSN-MME.
This measurement includes IPv6 datagrams counted by all ipv6StatsReasmOKs instances.

EntityDef.name: ipv6systemstatsreasmreqds
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of IPv6 fragments received and that need to be reassembled in the SGSN-MME.
This measurement includes IPv6 fragments counted by all ipv6StatsReasmReqds instances.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3areaasbdrrtrcount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of #AS# border routers reachable within this area. This number is initially zero, and is calculated in each #SPF# pass.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This gauge can only increase as a result of network reconfiguration. No actions are recommended.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3areabdrrtrcount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of area border routers reachable within this area. This number is initially zero, and is calculated in each #SPF# pass.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This gauge can only increase as a result of network reconfiguration. No actions are recommended.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3areascopelsacount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the total number of #LSA#s in the link-state database of this area, excluding #AS# external #LSA#s.
If #OSPF# #NSSA# is used within the area, this counter also includes Type 7 #LSA#s. In this case, it is possible that the supervised threshold needs to be increased.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Investigate why that many #LSA#s exist. It is possible that the network needs to be redesigned. Consider using #OSPF# #NSSA# to reduce the number of #LSA#s.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3areaspfruns
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of times that the intra-area route table is calculated using the link-state database of this area. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3asscopelsacount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #AS#-scope #LSA#s, such as AS external #LSA#s, in the link-state database.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3extlsacount
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of external (LS type 5) #LSA#s in the link-state database. The #SGSN-MME# supports a maximum of 8000 #LSA#s. Exceeding this limit can put the network at the risk because each new #LSA# makes #OSPF# convergence slower.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Investigate why so many external #LSA#s exist and which entity in the network that announces them. It is possible that the network needs to be redesigned. If #OSPF# #NSSA# is not used within the area, consider using it to reduce the number of external #LSA#s.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3originatenewlsas
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of new #LSAs# that are originated. The counter is incremented each time the router originates a new #LSA#.

EntityDef.name: ospfv3rxnewlsas
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #LSAs# received determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated #LSA#s.

EntityDef.name: bgpneighborfsmestablishedtransitions
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of times the #BGP# #FSM# is transitioned into the established state.

EntityDef.name: bgpneighborintotalmessages
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of BGP messages received from the remote peer on this connection.

EntityDef.name: bgpneighborinupdateelapsedtime
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the elapsed time, in seconds, since the last #BGP# UPDATE message was received from the neighbor. Each time the bgpNeighborInUpdates counter is incremented the value of this object is set to zero.
Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: A network failure might have occured in the network. Investigate if there are any problems with the #IP# connectivity at the interface board.

EntityDef.name: bgpneighborinupdates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #BGP# UPDATE messages received on this connection.

EntityDef.name: bgpneighborouttotalmessages
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of BGP messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection.

EntityDef.name: bgpneighboroutupdates
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #BGP# UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_nbrattachedecue_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached Extended Coverage (EC)-GSM IoT mode UEs. The gauge is incremented when an EC-GSM IoT mode UE sets the Coverage Class, for example during attach. The gauge is decremented when an EC-GSM IoT mode is detached or no longer has a Coverage Class set.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_nbrattachededrxue_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs using Extended Idle Mode Discontinuous Reception (eDRX). The gauge is incremented when a UE using eDRX attaches to or moves into SGSN. The gauge is decremented when a UE detaches from or moves out of SGSN, or deactivates eDRX.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingecueatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted Paging procedures initiated for Extended Coverage (EC)-GSM IoT mode UEs. The counter is incremented when the first Paging message is sent. Retransmissions of the same Paging message are not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingecuesucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful Paging procedures initiated for Extended Coverage (EC)-GSM IoT mode UEs. The counter is incremented when a Paging Response is received from the UE and when a message the UE sends is regarded as a Paging Response during the Paging procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxueatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of attempted paging procedures initiated for the UEs with Extended Idle Mode Discontinuous Reception (eDRX) mode activated. The counter is incremented when an eDRX Paging PS message is sent to the BSC. That is at the transmission of the first eDRX Paging PS message and retransmission is not counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxuerej_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of rejected Paging procedures initiated for the UEs using Extended Idle Mode Discontinuous Reception (eDRX). The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a Paging PS Reject message from the BSC.

EntityDef.name: vs_m2m_pagingedrxuesucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful Paging procedures initiated for the UEs using Extended Idle Mode Discontinuous Reception (eDRX), irrespective of the Paging being an initial eDRX Paging PS message or the resending of the eDRX Paging PS message. The counter is incremented when any valid LLC frame is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_attattach_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted E-UTRAN attach procedures initiated for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT within the MME's area.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_attachdecorrerouteout_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attach request procedures, where the MME sends a Reroute NAS Request message to the eNodeB for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_attachlapirejected_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Attach Requests from the low access priority UE when the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control is activated.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_attachnascongestioncontrolrejected_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of reject messages with T3346 and EMM cause code 22 (Congestion) sent by the MME for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT. The MME sends the reject messages in response to Attach Request due to the NAS Level Mobility Management Congestion Control based on the UE priority.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_attachuscdiscarded_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages discarded by the MME for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_attachuscrejected_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_emcattachuscdiscarded_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_11_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code11 (PLMN not allowed) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_12_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 12 (Tracking area not allowed) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_13_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 13 (Roaming not allowed in this tracking area) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_14_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 14 (EPS services not allowed in this PLMN) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_15_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 15 (No suitable cells in tracking area) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_17_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 17 (Network failure) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_19_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 19 (ESM failure) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_5_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 5 (IMEI not accepted) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_6_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 6 (Illegal ME) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_7_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code code 7 (EPS services not allowed) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_epsattachfail_8_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with an EMM cause code 8 (EPS services and non-EPS services not allowed) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_nbractattachedsub_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION:
This measurement provides the number of currently attached UEs using RAT type NB-IoT within an MME. The gauge is incremented when the UE enters the EMM-REGISTERED state, for example, because of Attach or Inter-MME TA Update. The gauge is decremented when the UE leaves the EMM-REGISTERED state, for example, because of Detach or Implicit Detach.
#Note: After a change to the #SAU# capacity license value, a small restart must be performed to update the default alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels. Manually configured alarm-triggering and alarm-clearing levels are not updated by a small restart. After a #SAU# capacity license value change, manually configured levels can be updated only by using the set_pm_sup CLI command.Note#

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_nbrcsattachedsub_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of SGs-associated UEs using RAT type NB-IoT within an MME. The SGs associations enable the UEs to perform the SMS service, the only CS service applicable for UEs using NB-IoT. The gauge is incremented at each successful initial UE registration towards an MSC/VLR. The gauge is decremented each time such a UE is IMSI detached.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_retrieveueinformation_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Retrieve UE Information procedures performed over the S1-MME interface. This counter is incremented each time the MME receives a Retrieve UE Information message over the S1-MME interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_succattach_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed E-UTRAN attach procedures initiated for UEs using RAT type NB IoT within the MMEs area. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an Attach Complete message.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_tauinteratt_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-MME #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#, for #UE#s in Tracking Areas with #RAT# type #NB-IoT#. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_tauintersucc_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Inter-MME #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#, for #UE#s in Tracking Areas with #RAT# type #NB-IoT#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_tauintraatt_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Periodic and Intra-MME #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#, for #UE#s in Tracking Areas with #RAT# type #NB-IoT#. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_tauintrasucc_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Periodic and Intra-MME #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#, for #UE#s in Tracking Areas with #RAT# type #NB-IoT#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_tauperiodicatt_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Periodic #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#, for #UE#s in Tracking Areas with #RAT# type #NB-IoT#. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_tauperiodicsucc_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Periodic #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#, for #UE#s in Tracking Areas with #RAT# type #NB-IoT#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_unsuccattach_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful E-UTRAN attach procedures initiated for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT within the MME's area. This counter is incremented whenever an Attach Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control. Note: The number of successful attempts subtracted from the total number of attempts does not equal the number of unsuccessful attempts due to discarded messages, resent messages,and messages controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_unsuccattachcc27_28_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with ESM cause codes 27 (Missing or unknown APN) and 28 (Unknown PDN type) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_mm_unsuccattachcc32_33_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with ESM cause codes 32 (Service option not supported) and 33 (Requested service option not subscribed) for UEs using RAT type NB-IoT.

EntityDef.name: vs_pool_attachthrottlingattachreservednotused_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the amount of unused Reserved Attach Rate allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach parameter. The presented gauge is the aggregrated value over the latest 60 seconds.

EntityDef.name: vs_pool_attachthrottlingnonreservedgranted_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Update Location Request (ULR) and Authentication Information Request (AIR) messages due to the Pool Move procedure that have been accepted by the Attach throttle using the non-reserved allowance. The non-reserved allowance is the difference between the total Attach throttle allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter, and the sum of the reserved allowances, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach and MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitGeoredRestore parameters. ULR and AIR messages accepted using the reserved Pool Move allowance specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitGeoredRestore parameter are not counted."

EntityDef.name: vs_pool_s6ablockbythrottle_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of S6a messages blocked due to the Attach Throttling function during Pool Move. The counter is incremented when an S6a message is blocked because the number of messages under throttling control exceeds the available allowance. The available allowance for Pool Move procedure messages is the difference between the total Attach throttle allowance, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter and the reserved allowance for E-UTRAN attach procedures, specified by the MMEAttachThrottlingReservedLimitAttach parameter.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sm_attactdefaultbearernonip_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted default bearer activations with PDN type Non-IP for devices with RAT type NB-IoT. The counter is incremented when a default bearer with PDN type Non-IP attempts to activate.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sm_nbractdefaultbearernonip_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active default bearers with PDN type Non-IP for devices with RAT type NB-IoT. The gauge is incremented when a new default bearer with PDN type Non-IP is activated and decremented when an active default bearer with PDN type Non-IP is deactivated.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sm_nbractdefaultbearernonipscef_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active default EPS bearers with PDN type Non-IP over the SCEF. The gauge is incremented when a new default EPS bearer with PDN type Non-IP over the SCEF is activated. The gauge is decremented when an active default EPS bearer with PDN type Non-IP over SCEF is deactivated.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sm_succactdefaultbearernonip_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successfully completed default bearer activations with PDN type Non-IP for devices with RAT type NB-IoT. The counter is incremented when a default bearer with PDN type Non-IP is successfully activated.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sm_ueinitiatedpdntransfercptoupswitchatt_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This counter is used to count the number of times of attempt of UE initiated switch to UP data transport in ECM_CONNECTED mode.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sm_ueinitiatedpdntransfercptoupswitchsucc_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This counter is used to count the number of times of successful procedures of UE initiated switch to UP data transport in ECM_CONNECTED mode.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mtlrctatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MT-LR procedures in the SGSN-MME. This measurement is indexed by LCS Client Type. The indexed counter is incremented when the MME receives a Provide Subscriber Location Request message from the GMLC over the SLg interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_mtlrctsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful MT-LR procedures in the SGSN-MME. The procedure is considered successful when the E-SMLC has provided an estimation of the UE's location. This measurement is indexed by LCS Client Type. The indexed counter is incremented when the MME sends the Provide Subscriber Location Response message to the GMLC over the SLg interface with a successful result code. Note: The number of successful MT-LR procedures for queued emergency SLg sessions are also counted.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestipctatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted location service request procedures in the SGSN-MME. This measurement is indexed by E-SMLC Primary IP Address and LCS Client Type. The indexed counter is incremented when the MME sends the LCS-AP Location Request message to the E-SMLC over the SLs interface.

EntityDef.name: vs_mm_locationrequestipctsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful location service request procedures in the SGSN-MME. This measurement is indexed by E-SMLC Primary IP Address and LCS Client Type. The indexed counter is incremented when the MME receives the LCS-AP Location Response message from the E-SMLC over the SLs interface with a successful result code.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_nbractsessions_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active Smp sessions in the SGSN for GSM network.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_nbruewithsession_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of UEs holding at least one active Smp session in the SGSN for GSM network.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sapcgwquery_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number that the SGSN queries the GGSN/PGW address that is returned by the SAPC for PDP connections in the GSM network. The counter is incremented each time the SGSN attempts to query the GGSN/PGW address and the GGSN/PGW address from SAPC is available. For example, the SGSN selects the GGSN/PGW from SAPC to establish PDP connections during a primary PDP context activation procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessioninitialatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session establishment in the SGSN for GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the INITIAL_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessioninitialsucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session establishments in the SGSN for GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN receives a successful Credit-Control-Answer message with the INITIAL_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionreauthatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempts of Smp session re-authorization from the SAPC to the SGSN from GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN receives a Re-Auth-Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionreauthsucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session re-authorization from the SAPC to the SGSN for GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a successful Re-Auth-Answer message.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionterminate_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Smp session termination procedures initiated by the SGSN for GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the TERMINATION_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionupdateatt_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Smp session update procedures initiated by the SGSN for GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN sends a Credit-Control-Request message with the UPDATE_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: vs_sx_sessionupdatesucc_g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Smp session update procedures initiated by the SGSN for GSM network. This counter is incremented each time the SGSN receives a successful Credit-Control-Answer message with the UPDATE_REQUEST type.

EntityDef.name: gsnoverloadprotectionignoredoutboundrequestssapc
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of outgoing request messages toward the SAPC that have been rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism in the GSM network. This counter is incremented each time a Credit-Control-Request message toward the SAPC is rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism. Note: This counter is now deprecated.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sec_authatt_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Authentication Request messages sent by the MME to NB-IoT UEs.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sec_authfailmme_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Authentication Reject messages sent by the MME to NB-IoT UEs.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sec_authfailue_20_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 20 (MAC failure) for NB-IoT UEs. The counter is increased whenever the NB-IoT UE detects an incorrect authentication parameter in the Authentication Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sec_authfailue_21_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 21 (Sync failure) for NB-IoT UEs. The counter is increased whenever the NB-IoT UE detects an incorrect SQN or a SQN is out of range.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_sec_authfailue_26_nb
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 26 (Non-EPS authentication unacceptable) for NB-IoT UEs. The counter is increased whenever the NB-IoT UE detects an incorrect authentication parameter in the Authentication Request message.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitcmrestablishmentatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Management Request messages sent from the MME to the SCEF over the T6a interface with a request for T6a connection establishment. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a Connection Management Request message to the SCEF with a request for connection establishment.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitcmrestablishmentsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Connection Management Answer messages sent from the SCEF to the MME over the T6a interface, indicating the successful establishment of the T6a connection to the SCEF. The counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a Connection Management Answer message indicating the successful establishment of the T6a connection to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitcmrreleaseatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Management Request messages sent from the MME to the SCEF over the T6a interface with a request for T6a connection release. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a Connection Management Request message to the SCEF with a request for connection release.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitcmrreleasesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Connection Management Answer messages sent from the SCEF to the MME over the T6a interface, indicating the successful release of the T6a connection to the SCEF. The counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a Connection Management Answer message indicating the successful release of the T6a connection to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitcmrupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Management Request messages sent from the MME to the SCEF over the T6a interface with a request for T6a connection update. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a Connection Management Request message to the SCEF with a request for connection update.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitcmrupdatesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Connection Management Answer messages sent from the SCEF to the MME over the T6a interface, indicating the successful update of the T6a connection to the SCEF. This counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a Connection Management Answer message indicating the successful update of the T6a connection to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitriratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Reporting Information Request messages sent from the MME to the SCEF. This counter is incremented each time the MME sends a Reporting Information Request message to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_mmeinitrirsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Reporting Information Request messages sent from the MME to the SCEF. This counter is incremented when the MME receives a Reporting Information Answer message from the SCEF indicating a successful procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_odratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Mobile Originated Data Request messages sent from the MME to the SCEF over the T6a interface. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a MO Data Request message to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_odrsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Mobile Originated Data Answer messages sent from the SCEF to the MME. The counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a successful MO Data Answer message from the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_scefinitcmrreleaseatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Management Request messages sent from the SCEF to the MME over the T6a interface with a request for T6a connection release. The counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a Connection Management Request message from the SCEF with a request for connection release.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_scefinitcmrreleasesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Connection Management Answer messages sent from the MME to the SCEF over the T6a interface, indicating the successful release of the T6a connection to the SCEF. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a Connection Management Answer message indicating the successful release of the T6a connection to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_scefinitcmrupdateatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Connection Management Request messages sent from the SCEF to the MME over the T6a interface with a request for T6a connection update. The counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a Connection Management Request message from the SCEF with a request for connection update.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_scefinitcmrupdatesucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Connection Management Answer messages sent from the MME to the SCEF over the T6a interface, indicating the successful update of the T6a connection to the SCEF. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a Connection Management Answer message indicating the successful update of the T6a connection to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_tdratt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of Mobile Terminated Data Request messages sent from the SCEF to the MME over the T6a interface. The counter is incremented each time when the MME receives a MT Data Request message from the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_tdrfailduetouetempunreachable_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Mobile Terminated Data Answer messages sent from the MME to the SCEF that have failed with a result code "DIAMETER_ERROR_USER_TEMPORARILY_UNREACHABLE (5653)" for the following reasons: 1.The UE is in PSM or eDRX. 2.No paging response is received from the UE after the SCEF Wait Time expires.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_t6a_tdrsucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful Mobile Terminated Data Answer messages sent from the MME to the SCEF. The counter is incremented each time when the MME sends a successful MT Data Answer message to the SCEF.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_monte_nbrcommunicationfailure_e

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_monte_nbrlocationreporting_e

This gauge is incremented with every new Location Reporting monitoring event configuration and decremented when a Location Reporting configuration has been fully reported or deleted.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_monte_nbrlossofconnectivity_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active Loss of Connectivity monitoring event configurations. This gauge is incremented with every new Loss of Connectivity monitoring event configuration and decremented when a Loss of Connectivity configuration has been fully reported or deleted.

EntityDef.name: vs_iot_monte_nbruereachability_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of active UE Reachability monitoring event configurations. This gauge is incremented with every new UE Reachability monitoring event configuration and decremented when a UE Reachability configuration has been fully reported or deleted.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgd_mosmsatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MO-SMS Message Forwarding procedures initiated by the MME over the SGd interface. This counter is incremented when the MME sends an MO Forward Short Message Request message to the SMS-IWMSC.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgd_mosmssucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful MO-SMS Message Forwarding procedures initiated by the MME over the SGd interface. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an MO Forward Short Message Answer message with success from the SMS-IWMSC.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgd_mtsmsatt_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted MT-SMS Message Forwarding procedures initiated by the SMS-GMSC over the SGd interface. This counter is incremented when the MME receives an MT Forward Short Message Request message from the SMS-GMSC.

EntityDef.name: vs_sgd_mtsmssucc_e
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful MT-SMS Message Forwarding procedures initiated by the SMS-GMSC over the SGd interface. This counter is incremented when the MME sends an MT Forward Short Message Answer message with success to the SMS-GMSC.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_n2release_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of N2 releases in the AMF. Both NG-RAN and AMF initiated releases are counted. Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the NG-RAN.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_n2releaseradioconnectionlost_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of N2 Releases initiated by the AMF when it receives the 'UE Context Release Request' message with the Cause 'Radio connection with UE lost' from the NG-RAN. The counter is incremented when the AMF sends the 'UE Context Release Command' message as a response to the 'UE Context Release Request' message with the Cause 'Radio connection with UE lost', from the NG-RAN.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_n2releaseredirection_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of N2 Releases initiated by the AMF when it receives the 'UE Context Release Request' message with the Cause 'Redirection' from the NG-RAN. The counter is incremented when the AMF sends the 'UE Context Release Command' message to the NG-RAN as a response to the 'UE Context Release Request' message with the Cause 'Redirection', from the NG-RAN.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_n2releasereq_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of N2 releases request received in the AMF. Trigger: Receiving UE Context Release Request initiated by NG-RAN.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_n2releaseuserinactivity_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of NG-RAN-initiated N2 releases due to cause "User Inactivity". Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the NG-RAN, after receiving a UE Context Release Request from the NG-RAN with cause "User Inactivity".

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_pagingatt_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of paging messages sent by the AMF. The counter is incremented when a paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message with the current S-TMSI in the procedure.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_pagingsucc_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any N1 message from UE is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_servicereqdataatt_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures in the AMF. It is incremented when an Service Request with service type IE set to 'data' is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_servicereqdataunsucc_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Service Request procedures in the AMF. It is incremented when an Service Request with service type IE set to data is received from the UE and Service Reject message is sent to UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_servicereqmtatt_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures in the AMF. It is incremented when an Service Request with service type IE 'mobile terminated services' is received.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_servicereqmtunsucc_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Service Request procedures in the AMF. It is incremented when an Service Request with service type IE set to 'mobile terminated services' is received from the UE and Service Reject message is sent to UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_servicereqsignallingatt_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures in the AMF. It is incremented when an Service Request with service type IE set to 'signalling' is received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_5gmm_servicereqsignallingunsucc_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Service Request procedures in the AMF. It is incremented when an Service Request with service type IE set to 'signalling' is received from the UE and Service Reject message is sent to UE.

EntityDef.name: vs_rm_reginitreq_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of initial registration requests received by the AMF.

EntityDef.name: vs_rm_reginitsucc_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful initial registrations at the AMF.

EntityDef.name: vs_rm_registeredsubnbr_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of currently registered #NPS# subscribers within this #AMF# area. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when the #UE# enters or leaves the #AMF#, for example, due to Registration, Inter-#AMF# #TA# Update, Deregistration or Implicit Deregistration Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a small restart when the #SAU# capacity license value is changed.

EntityDef.name: vs_nrf_nfdiscovercachehit_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of #NG_RAN# Nnrf_NFDiscovery requests that was responded from the local cache and not resulted in signaling to external NRF. Trigger: Returning Nnrf_NFDiscovery SearchResult from local cache.

EntityDef.name: vs_nrf_nfdiscoversucc_5g
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of successful #NG_RAN# Nnrf_NFDiscovery responses received from NRF. Trigger: Reception of the Nnrf_NFDiscovery response from the NRF with a successful result code.

EntityDef.name: nbrapsyncfailed
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This counter provides the number of suppressed AP restarts due to synchronization failure between APs caused by the TCP connection between them is lost.

EntityDef.name: nbraptakeovertimeout
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This counter provides the number of suppressed large restarts when the Overall Recovery Timer expires during an AP takeover and AP loss or AP gain is ongoing.

EntityDef.name: nbrconnectioncleanupfailed
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the total number of suppressed small restarts, DP restarts, or both, small restarts and DP restarts, if time-outs occur during a connection data cleanup procedure. The counter is incremented when a possible small restart or a DP restart is skipped if time-outs occur during a connection data cleanup procedure.

EntityDef.name: nbrslrescalationskipped
EntityDef.ENTITY_DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of suppressed escalations from a small local restart. The counter is incremented when a possible small restart is skipped after three small local restarts on the same AP during a 15-minute time interval.
